401 ----
402 SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerSELECT(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const { 0
403 if(!Subtarget.hasMips32r6()) 0
404 return MipsTargetLowering::LowerOperation(Op, DAG); 0
405 ----
406 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
407 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
408 ----
409 // Although MTC1_D64 takes an i32 and writes an f64, the upper 32 bits of the ----
410 // floating point register are undefined. Not really an issue as sel.d, which ----
411 // is produced from an FSELECT node, only looks at bit 0. ----
412 SDValue Tmp = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::MTC1_D64, DL, MVT::f64, Op->getOperand(0)); 0
413 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::FSELECT, DL, ResTy, Tmp, Op->getOperand(1), 0
414 Op->getOperand(2)); 0
415 } 0
416 ----

418 EVT VT, unsigned, Align, MachineMemOperand::Flags, unsigned *Fast) const { ----

421 if (Subtarget.systemSupportsUnalignedAccess()) { 0

423 // implementation defined whether this is handled by hardware, software, or ----
424 // a hybrid of the two but it's expected that most implementations will ----
425 // handle the majority of cases in hardware. ----
426 if (Fast) 0
427 *Fast = 1; 0
428 return true; 0
429 } ----
430 ----
431 switch (SVT) { 0
432 case MVT::i64: 0
433 case MVT::i32: ----
434 if (Fast) 0
435 *Fast = 1; 0
436 return true; 0
437 default: 0
438 return false; 0
439 } ----
440 } ----

468 // Fold zero extensions into MipsISD::VEXTRACT_[SZ]EXT_ELT ----
469 // ----
470 // Performs the following transformations: ----
471 // - Changes MipsISD::VEXTRACT_[SZ]EXT_ELT to zero extension if its ----
472 // sign/zero-extension is completely overwritten by the new one performed by ----
473 // the ISD::AND. ----
474 // - Removes redundant zero extensions performed by an ISD::AND. ----
475 static SDValue performANDCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
476 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
477 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
478 if (!Subtarget.hasMSA()) 0
479 return SDValue(); 0
480 ----
481 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0); 0
482 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1); 0
483 unsigned Op0Opcode = Op0->getOpcode(); 0
484 ----
485 // (and (MipsVExtract[SZ]Ext $a, $b, $c), imm:$d) ----
486 // where $d + 1 == 2^n and n == 32 ----
487 // or $d + 1 == 2^n and n <= 32 and ZExt ----
488 // -> (MipsVExtractZExt $a, $b, $c) ----
489 if (Op0Opcode == MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT || 0
490 Op0Opcode == MipsISD::VEXTRACT_ZEXT_ELT) { ----
491 ConstantSDNode *Mask = dyn_cast(Op1); 0
492 ----
493 if (!Mask) 0
494 return SDValue(); 0
495 ----
496 int32_t Log2IfPositive = (Mask->getAPIntValue() + 1).exactLogBase2(); 0
497 ----
498 if (Log2IfPositive <= 0) 0
499 return SDValue(); // Mask+1 is not a power of 2 0
500 ----
501 SDValue Op0Op2 = Op0->getOperand(2); 0
502 EVT ExtendTy = cast(Op0Op2)->getVT(); 0
503 unsigned ExtendTySize = ExtendTy.getSizeInBits(); 0
504 unsigned Log2 = Log2IfPositive; 0
505 ----
506 if ((Op0Opcode == MipsISD::VEXTRACT_ZEXT_ELT && Log2 >= ExtendTySize) || 0
507 Log2 == ExtendTySize) { ----
508 SDValue Ops[] = { Op0->getOperand(0), Op0->getOperand(1), Op0Op2 }; 0
509 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VEXTRACT_ZEXT_ELT, SDLoc(Op0), 0
510 Op0->getVTList(), ----
511 ArrayRef(Ops, Op0->getNumOperands())); 0
512 } ----
513 } ----
514 ----
515 return SDValue(); 0
516 } ----
517 ----
518 // Determine if the specified node is a constant vector splat. ----
519 // ----
520 // Returns true and sets Imm if: ----
521 // * N is a ISD::BUILD_VECTOR representing a constant splat ----
522 // ----
523 // This function is quite similar to MipsSEDAGToDAGISel::selectVSplat. The ----
524 // differences are that it assumes the MSA has already been checked and the ----
525 // arbitrary requirement for a maximum of 32-bit integers isn't applied (and ----
526 // must not be in order for binsri.d to be selectable). ----
527 static bool isVSplat(SDValue N, APInt &Imm, bool IsLittleEndian) { 0
528 BuildVectorSDNode *Node = dyn_cast(N.getNode()); 0
529 ----
530 if (!Node) 0
531 return false; 0
532 ----
533 APInt SplatValue, SplatUndef; 0
534 unsigned SplatBitSize; ----
535 bool HasAnyUndefs; ----
536 ----
537 if (!Node->isConstantSplat(SplatValue, SplatUndef, SplatBitSize, HasAnyUndefs, 0
538 8, !IsLittleEndian)) 0
539 return false; 0
540 ----
541 Imm = SplatValue; 0
542 ----
543 return true; 0
544 } 0
545 ----
546 // Test whether the given node is an all-ones build_vector. ----
547 static bool isVectorAllOnes(SDValue N) { 0
548 // Look through bitcasts. Endianness doesn't matter because we are looking ----
549 // for an all-ones value. ----
550 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST) 0
551 N = N->getOperand(0); 0
552 ----
553 BuildVectorSDNode *BVN = dyn_cast(N); 0
554 ----
555 if (!BVN) 0
556 return false; 0
557 ----
558 APInt SplatValue, SplatUndef; 0
559 unsigned SplatBitSize; ----
560 bool HasAnyUndefs; ----
561 ----
562 // Endianness doesn't matter in this context because we are looking for ----
563 // an all-ones value. ----
564 if (BVN->isConstantSplat(SplatValue, SplatUndef, SplatBitSize, HasAnyUndefs)) 0
565 return SplatValue.isAllOnes(); 0
566 ----
567 return false; 0
568 } 0
569 ----
570 // Test whether N is the bitwise inverse of OfNode. ----
571 static bool isBitwiseInverse(SDValue N, SDValue OfNode) { 0
572 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::XOR) 0
573 return false; 0
574 ----
575 if (isVectorAllOnes(N->getOperand(0))) 0
576 return N->getOperand(1) == OfNode; 0
577 ----
578 if (isVectorAllOnes(N->getOperand(1))) 0
579 return N->getOperand(0) == OfNode; 0
580 ----
581 return false; 0
582 } ----
583 ----
584 // Perform combines where ISD::OR is the root node. ----
585 // ----
586 // Performs the following transformations: ----
587 // - (or (and $a, $mask), (and $b, $inv_mask)) => (vselect $mask, $a, $b) ----
588 // where $inv_mask is the bitwise inverse of $mask and the 'or' has a 128-bit ----
589 // vector type. ----
590 static SDValue performORCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
591 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
592 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
593 if (!Subtarget.hasMSA()) 0
594 return SDValue(); 0
595 ----
596 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0); 0
597 ----
598 if (!Ty.is128BitVector()) 0
599 return SDValue(); 0
600 ----
601 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0); 0
602 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1); 0
603 ----
604 if (Op0->getOpcode() == ISD::AND && Op1->getOpcode() == ISD::AND) { 0
605 SDValue Op0Op0 = Op0->getOperand(0); 0
606 SDValue Op0Op1 = Op0->getOperand(1); 0
607 SDValue Op1Op0 = Op1->getOperand(0); 0
608 SDValue Op1Op1 = Op1->getOperand(1); 0
609 bool IsLittleEndian = !Subtarget.isLittle(); 0
610 ----
611 SDValue IfSet, IfClr, Cond; 0
612 bool IsConstantMask = false; 0
613 APInt Mask, InvMask; 0
614 ----
615 // If Op0Op0 is an appropriate mask, try to find it's inverse in either ----
616 // Op1Op0, or Op1Op1. Keep track of the Cond, IfSet, and IfClr nodes, while ----
617 // looking. ----
618 // IfClr will be set if we find a valid match. ----
619 if (isVSplat(Op0Op0, Mask, IsLittleEndian)) { 0
620 Cond = Op0Op0; 0
621 IfSet = Op0Op1; 0
622 ----
623 if (isVSplat(Op1Op0, InvMask, IsLittleEndian) && 0
624 Mask.getBitWidth() == InvMask.getBitWidth() && Mask == ~InvMask) 0
625 IfClr = Op1Op1; 0
626 else if (isVSplat(Op1Op1, InvMask, IsLittleEndian) && 0
627 Mask.getBitWidth() == InvMask.getBitWidth() && Mask == ~InvMask) 0
628 IfClr = Op1Op0; 0
629 ----
630 IsConstantMask = true; 0
631 } ----
632 ----
633 // If IfClr is not yet set, and Op0Op1 is an appropriate mask, try the same ----
634 // thing again using this mask. ----
635 // IfClr will be set if we find a valid match. ----
636 if (!IfClr.getNode() && isVSplat(Op0Op1, Mask, IsLittleEndian)) { 0
637 Cond = Op0Op1; 0
638 IfSet = Op0Op0; 0
639 ----
640 if (isVSplat(Op1Op0, InvMask, IsLittleEndian) && 0
641 Mask.getBitWidth() == InvMask.getBitWidth() && Mask == ~InvMask) 0
642 IfClr = Op1Op1; 0
643 else if (isVSplat(Op1Op1, InvMask, IsLittleEndian) && 0
644 Mask.getBitWidth() == InvMask.getBitWidth() && Mask == ~InvMask) 0
645 IfClr = Op1Op0; 0
646 ----
647 IsConstantMask = true; 0
648 } ----
649 ----
650 // If IfClr is not yet set, try looking for a non-constant match. ----
651 // IfClr will be set if we find a valid match amongst the eight ----
652 // possibilities. ----
653 if (!IfClr.getNode()) { 0
654 if (isBitwiseInverse(Op0Op0, Op1Op0)) { 0
655 Cond = Op1Op0; 0
656 IfSet = Op1Op1; 0
657 IfClr = Op0Op1; 0
658 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op0Op1, Op1Op0)) { 0
659 Cond = Op1Op0; 0
660 IfSet = Op1Op1; 0
661 IfClr = Op0Op0; 0
662 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op0Op0, Op1Op1)) { 0
663 Cond = Op1Op1; 0
664 IfSet = Op1Op0; 0
665 IfClr = Op0Op1; 0
666 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op0Op1, Op1Op1)) { 0
667 Cond = Op1Op1; 0
668 IfSet = Op1Op0; 0
669 IfClr = Op0Op0; 0
670 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op1Op0, Op0Op0)) { 0
671 Cond = Op0Op0; 0
672 IfSet = Op0Op1; 0
673 IfClr = Op1Op1; 0
674 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op1Op1, Op0Op0)) { 0
675 Cond = Op0Op0; 0
676 IfSet = Op0Op1; 0
677 IfClr = Op1Op0; 0
678 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op1Op0, Op0Op1)) { 0
679 Cond = Op0Op1; 0
680 IfSet = Op0Op0; 0
681 IfClr = Op1Op1; 0
682 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op1Op1, Op0Op1)) { 0
683 Cond = Op0Op1; 0
684 IfSet = Op0Op0; 0
685 IfClr = Op1Op0; 0
686 } ----
687 } ----
688 ----
689 // At this point, IfClr will be set if we have a valid match. ----
690 if (!IfClr.getNode()) 0
691 return SDValue(); 0
692 ----
693 assert(Cond.getNode() && IfSet.getNode()); 0
694 ----
695 // Fold degenerate cases. ----
696 if (IsConstantMask) { 0
697 if (Mask.isAllOnes()) 0
698 return IfSet; 0
699 else if (Mask == 0) 0
700 return IfClr; 0
701 } ----
702 ----
703 // Transform the DAG into an equivalent VSELECT. ----
704 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, SDLoc(N), Ty, Cond, IfSet, IfClr); 0
705 } 0
706 ----
707 return SDValue(); 0
708 } ----
709 ----
710 static bool shouldTransformMulToShiftsAddsSubs(APInt C, EVT VT, 0
711 SelectionDAG &DAG, ----
712 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
713 // Estimate the number of operations the below transform will turn a ----
714 // constant multiply into. The number is approximately equal to the minimal ----
715 // number of powers of two that constant can be broken down to by adding ----
716 // or subtracting them. ----
717 // ----
718 // If we have taken more than 12[1] / 8[2] steps to attempt the ----
719 // optimization for a native sized value, it is more than likely that this ----
720 // optimization will make things worse. ----
721 // ----
722 // [1] MIPS64 requires 6 instructions at most to materialize any constant, ----
723 // multiplication requires at least 4 cycles, but another cycle (or two) ----
724 // to retrieve the result from the HI/LO registers. ----
725 // ----
726 // [2] For MIPS32, more than 8 steps is expensive as the constant could be ----
727 // materialized in 2 instructions, multiplication requires at least 4 ----
728 // cycles, but another cycle (or two) to retrieve the result from the ----
729 // HI/LO registers. ----
730 // ----
731 // TODO: ----
732 // - MaxSteps needs to consider the `VT` of the constant for the current ----
733 // target. ----
734 // - Consider to perform this optimization after type legalization. ----
735 // That allows to remove a workaround for types not supported natively. ----
736 // - Take in account `-Os, -Oz` flags because this optimization ----
737 // increases code size. ----
738 unsigned MaxSteps = Subtarget.isABI_O32() ? 8 : 12; 0
739 ----
740 SmallVector WorkStack(1, C); 0
741 unsigned Steps = 0; 0
742 unsigned BitWidth = C.getBitWidth(); 0
743 ----
744 while (!WorkStack.empty()) { 0
745 APInt Val = WorkStack.pop_back_val(); 0
746 ----
747 if (Val == 0 || Val == 1) 0
748 continue; 0
749 ----
750 if (Steps >= MaxSteps) 0
751 return false; 0
752 ----
753 if (Val.isPowerOf2()) { 0
754 ++Steps; 0
755 continue; 0
756 } ----
757 ----
758 APInt Floor = APInt(BitWidth, 1) << Val.logBase2(); 0
759 APInt Ceil = Val.isNegative() ? APInt(BitWidth, 0) 0
760 : APInt(BitWidth, 1) << C.ceilLogBase2(); 0
761 if ((Val - Floor).ule(Ceil - Val)) { 0
762 WorkStack.push_back(Floor); 0
763 WorkStack.push_back(Val - Floor); 0
764 } else { ----
765 WorkStack.push_back(Ceil); 0
766 WorkStack.push_back(Ceil - Val); 0
767 } ----
768 ----
769 ++Steps; 0
770 } 0
771 ----
772 // If the value being multiplied is not supported natively, we have to pay ----
773 // an additional legalization cost, conservatively assume an increase in the ----
774 // cost of 3 instructions per step. This values for this heuristic were ----
775 // determined experimentally. ----
776 unsigned RegisterSize = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo() 0
777 .getRegisterType(*DAG.getContext(), VT) 0
778 .getSizeInBits(); 0
779 Steps *= (VT.getSizeInBits() != RegisterSize) * 3; 0
780 if (Steps > 27) 0
781 return false; 0
782 ----
783 return true; 0
784 } 0
785 ----
786 static SDValue genConstMult(SDValue X, APInt C, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT, 0
787 EVT ShiftTy, SelectionDAG &DAG) { ----
788 // Return 0. ----
789 if (C == 0) 0
790 return DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT); 0
791 ----
792 // Return x. ----
793 if (C == 1) 0
794 return X; 0
795 ----
796 // If c is power of 2, return (shl x, log2(c)). ----
797 if (C.isPowerOf2()) 0
798 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, X, 0
799 DAG.getConstant(C.logBase2(), DL, ShiftTy)); 0
800 ----
801 unsigned BitWidth = C.getBitWidth(); 0
802 APInt Floor = APInt(BitWidth, 1) << C.logBase2(); 0
803 APInt Ceil = C.isNegative() ? APInt(BitWidth, 0) : 0
804 APInt(BitWidth, 1) << C.ceilLogBase2(); 0
805 ----
806 // If |c - floor_c| <= |c - ceil_c|, ----
807 // where floor_c = pow(2, floor(log2(c))) and ceil_c = pow(2, ceil(log2(c))), ----
808 // return (add constMult(x, floor_c), constMult(x, c - floor_c)). ----
809 if ((C - Floor).ule(Ceil - C)) { 0
810 SDValue Op0 = genConstMult(X, Floor, DL, VT, ShiftTy, DAG); 0
811 SDValue Op1 = genConstMult(X, C - Floor, DL, VT, ShiftTy, DAG); 0
812 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, Op0, Op1); 0
813 } ----
814 ----
815 // If |c - floor_c| > |c - ceil_c|, ----
816 // return (sub constMult(x, ceil_c), constMult(x, ceil_c - c)). ----
817 SDValue Op0 = genConstMult(X, Ceil, DL, VT, ShiftTy, DAG); 0
818 SDValue Op1 = genConstMult(X, Ceil - C, DL, VT, ShiftTy, DAG); 0
819 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, Op0, Op1); 0
820 } 0
821 ----
822 static SDValue performMULCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
823 const TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
824 const MipsSETargetLowering *TL, ----
825 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
826 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0); 0
827 ----
828 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(N->getOperand(1))) 0
829 if (!VT.isVector() && shouldTransformMulToShiftsAddsSubs( 0
830 C->getAPIntValue(), VT, DAG, Subtarget)) ----
831 return genConstMult(N->getOperand(0), C->getAPIntValue(), SDLoc(N), VT, 0
832 TL->getScalarShiftAmountTy(DAG.getDataLayout(), VT), 0
833 DAG); 0
834 ----
835 return SDValue(N, 0); 0
836 } ----

838 static SDValue performDSPShiftCombine(unsigned Opc, SDNode *N, EVT Ty, 0
839 SelectionDAG &DAG, ----
840 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
841 // See if this is a vector splat immediate node. ----
842 APInt SplatValue, SplatUndef; 0
843 unsigned SplatBitSize; ----
844 bool HasAnyUndefs; ----
845 unsigned EltSize = Ty.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
846 BuildVectorSDNode *BV = dyn_cast(N->getOperand(1)); 0
847 ----
848 if (!Subtarget.hasDSP()) 0
849 return SDValue(); 0
850 ----
851 if (!BV || 0
852 !BV->isConstantSplat(SplatValue, SplatUndef, SplatBitSize, HasAnyUndefs, 0
853 EltSize, !Subtarget.isLittle()) || 0
854 (SplatBitSize != EltSize) || 0
855 (SplatValue.getZExtValue() >= EltSize)) 0
856 return SDValue(); 0
857 ----
858 SDLoc DL(N); 0
859 return DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, Ty, N->getOperand(0), 0
860 DAG.getConstant(SplatValue.getZExtValue(), DL, MVT::i32)); 0
861 } 0
862 ----
863 static SDValue performSHLCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
864 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
865 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
866 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0); 0
867 ----
868 if ((Ty != MVT::v2i16) && (Ty != MVT::v4i8)) 0
869 return SDValue(); 0
870 ----
871 return performDSPShiftCombine(MipsISD::SHLL_DSP, N, Ty, DAG, Subtarget); 0
872 } ----
873 ----
874 // Fold sign-extensions into MipsISD::VEXTRACT_[SZ]EXT_ELT for MSA and fold ----
875 // constant splats into MipsISD::SHRA_DSP for DSPr2. ----
876 // ----
877 // Performs the following transformations: ----
878 // - Changes MipsISD::VEXTRACT_[SZ]EXT_ELT to sign extension if its ----
879 // sign/zero-extension is completely overwritten by the new one performed by ----
880 // the ISD::SRA and ISD::SHL nodes. ----
881 // - Removes redundant sign extensions performed by an ISD::SRA and ISD::SHL ----
882 // sequence. ----
883 // ----
884 // See performDSPShiftCombine for more information about the transformation ----
885 // used for DSPr2. ----
886 static SDValue performSRACombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
887 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
888 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
889 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0); 0
890 ----
891 if (Subtarget.hasMSA()) { 0
892 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0); 0
893 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1); 0
894 ----
895 // (sra (shl (MipsVExtract[SZ]Ext $a, $b, $c), imm:$d), imm:$d) ----
896 // where $d + sizeof($c) == 32 ----
897 // or $d + sizeof($c) <= 32 and SExt ----
898 // -> (MipsVExtractSExt $a, $b, $c) ----
899 if (Op0->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && Op1 == Op0->getOperand(1)) { 0
900 SDValue Op0Op0 = Op0->getOperand(0); 0
901 ConstantSDNode *ShAmount = dyn_cast(Op1); 0
902 ----
903 if (!ShAmount) 0
904 return SDValue(); 0
905 ----
906 if (Op0Op0->getOpcode() != MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT && 0
907 Op0Op0->getOpcode() != MipsISD::VEXTRACT_ZEXT_ELT) 0
908 return SDValue(); 0
909 ----
910 EVT ExtendTy = cast(Op0Op0->getOperand(2))->getVT(); 0
911 unsigned TotalBits = ShAmount->getZExtValue() + ExtendTy.getSizeInBits(); 0
912 ----
913 if (TotalBits == 32 || 0
914 (Op0Op0->getOpcode() == MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT && 0
915 TotalBits <= 32)) { ----
916 SDValue Ops[] = { Op0Op0->getOperand(0), Op0Op0->getOperand(1), 0
917 Op0Op0->getOperand(2) }; 0
918 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT, SDLoc(Op0Op0), 0
919 Op0Op0->getVTList(), ----
920 ArrayRef(Ops, Op0Op0->getNumOperands())); 0
921 } ----
922 } ----
923 } ----
924 ----
925 if ((Ty != MVT::v2i16) && ((Ty != MVT::v4i8) || !Subtarget.hasDSPR2())) 0
926 return SDValue(); 0
927 ----
928 return performDSPShiftCombine(MipsISD::SHRA_DSP, N, Ty, DAG, Subtarget); 0
929 } ----
930 ----

932 static SDValue performSRLCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
933 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
934 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
935 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0); 0
936 ----
937 if (((Ty != MVT::v2i16) || !Subtarget.hasDSPR2()) && (Ty != MVT::v4i8)) 0
938 return SDValue(); 0
939 ----
940 return performDSPShiftCombine(MipsISD::SHRL_DSP, N, Ty, DAG, Subtarget); 0
941 } ----
942 ----
943 static bool isLegalDSPCondCode(EVT Ty, ISD::CondCode CC) { 0
944 bool IsV216 = (Ty == MVT::v2i16); 0
945 ----
946 switch (CC) { 0
947 case ISD::SETEQ: 0
948 case ISD::SETNE: return true; 0
949 case ISD::SETLT: 0
950 case ISD::SETLE: ----
951 case ISD::SETGT: ----
952 case ISD::SETGE: return IsV216; 0
953 case ISD::SETULT: 0
954 case ISD::SETULE: ----
955 case ISD::SETUGT: ----
956 case ISD::SETUGE: return !IsV216; 0
957 default: return false; 0
958 } ----
959 } ----
960 ----
961 static SDValue performSETCCCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) { 0
962 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0); 0
963 ----
964 if ((Ty != MVT::v2i16) && (Ty != MVT::v4i8)) 0
965 return SDValue(); 0
966 ----
967 if (!isLegalDSPCondCode(Ty, cast(N->getOperand(2))->get())) 0
968 return SDValue(); 0
969 ----
970 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::SETCC_DSP, SDLoc(N), Ty, N->getOperand(0), 0
971 N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2)); 0
972 } ----
973 ----
974 static SDValue performVSELECTCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) { 0
975 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0); 0
976 ----
977 if (Ty == MVT::v2i16 || Ty == MVT::v4i8) { 0
978 SDValue SetCC = N->getOperand(0); 0
979 ----
980 if (SetCC.getOpcode() != MipsISD::SETCC_DSP) 0
981 return SDValue(); 0
982 ----
983 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::SELECT_CC_DSP, SDLoc(N), Ty, 0
984 SetCC.getOperand(0), SetCC.getOperand(1), 0
985 N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2), SetCC.getOperand(2)); 0
986 } ----
987 ----
988 return SDValue(); 0
989 } ----
990 ----
991 static SDValue performXORCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
992 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
993 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0); 0
994 ----
995 if (Subtarget.hasMSA() && Ty.is128BitVector() && Ty.isInteger()) { 0
996 // Try the following combines: ----
997 // (xor (or $a, $b), (build_vector allones)) ----
998 // (xor (or $a, $b), (bitcast (build_vector allones))) ----
999 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0); 0
1000 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1); 0
1001 SDValue NotOp; 0
1002 ----
1003 if (ISD::isBuildVectorAllOnes(Op0.getNode())) 0
1004 NotOp = Op1; 0
1005 else if (ISD::isBuildVectorAllOnes(Op1.getNode())) 0
1006 NotOp = Op0; 0
1007 else ----
1008 return SDValue(); 0
1009 ----
1010 if (NotOp->getOpcode() == ISD::OR) 0
1011 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VNOR, SDLoc(N), Ty, NotOp->getOperand(0), 0
1012 NotOp->getOperand(1)); 0
1013 } ----
1014 ----
1015 return SDValue(); 0
1016 } ----

1135 ----
1136 bool MipsSETargetLowering::isEligibleForTailCallOptimization( 0
1137 const CCState &CCInfo, unsigned NextStackOffset, ----
1138 const MipsFunctionInfo &FI) const { ----
1139 if (!UseMipsTailCalls) 0
1140 return false; 0
1141 ----
1142 // Exception has to be cleared with eret. ----
1143 if (FI.isISR()) 0
1144 return false; 0
1145 ----
1146 // Return false if either the callee or caller has a byval argument. ----
1147 if (CCInfo.getInRegsParamsCount() > 0 || FI.hasByvalArg()) 0
1148 return false; 0
1149 ----
1150 // Return true if the callee's argument area is no larger than the ----
1151 // caller's. ----
1152 return NextStackOffset <= FI.getIncomingArgSize(); 0
1153 } ----

1164 Chain); ----

1225 SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerBITCAST(SDValue Op, 0
1226 SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
1227 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
1228 MVT Src = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType().getSimpleVT(); 0
1229 MVT Dest = Op.getValueType().getSimpleVT(); 0
1230 ----
1231 // Bitcast i64 to double. ----
1232 if (Src == MVT::i64 && Dest == MVT::f64) { 0
1233 SDValue Lo, Hi; 0
1234 std::tie(Lo, Hi) = 0
1235 DAG.SplitScalar(Op.getOperand(0), DL, MVT::i32, MVT::i32); 0
1236 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::BuildPairF64, DL, MVT::f64, Lo, Hi); 0
1237 } ----
1238 ----
1239 // Bitcast double to i64. ----
1240 if (Src == MVT::f64 && Dest == MVT::i64) { 0
1241 SDValue Lo = ----
1242 DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(0), 0
1243 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1244 SDValue Hi = ----
1245 DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(0), 0
1246 DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1247 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, DL, MVT::i64, Lo, Hi); 0
1248 } ----
1249 ----
1250 // Skip other cases of bitcast and use default lowering. ----
1251 return SDValue(); 0
1252 } 0
1253 ----
1254 SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerMulDiv(SDValue Op, unsigned NewOpc, 0
1255 bool HasLo, bool HasHi, ----
1256 SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
1257 // MIPS32r6/MIPS64r6 removed accumulator based multiplies. ----
1258 assert(!Subtarget.hasMips32r6()); 0
1259 ----
1260 EVT Ty = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType(); 0
1261 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
1262 SDValue Mult = DAG.getNode(NewOpc, DL, MVT::Untyped, 0
1263 Op.getOperand(0), Op.getOperand(1)); 0
1264 SDValue Lo, Hi; 0
1265 ----
1266 if (HasLo) 0
1267 Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::MFLO, DL, Ty, Mult); 0
1268 if (HasHi) 0
1269 Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::MFHI, DL, Ty, Mult); 0
1270 ----
1271 if (!HasLo || !HasHi) 0
1272 return HasLo ? Lo : Hi; 0
1273 ----
1274 SDValue Vals[] = { Lo, Hi }; 0
1275 return DAG.getMergeValues(Vals, DL); 0
1276 } 0
1277 ----
1278 static SDValue initAccumulator(SDValue In, const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) { 0
1279 SDValue InLo, InHi; 0
1280 std::tie(InLo, InHi) = DAG.SplitScalar(In, DL, MVT::i32, MVT::i32); 0
1281 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::MTLOHI, DL, MVT::Untyped, InLo, InHi); 0
1282 } ----
1283 ----
1284 static SDValue extractLOHI(SDValue Op, const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) { 0
1285 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::MFLO, DL, MVT::i32, Op); 0
1286 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::MFHI, DL, MVT::i32, Op); 0
1287 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, DL, MVT::i64, Lo, Hi); 0
1288 } ----
1289 ----
1290 // This function expands mips intrinsic nodes which have 64-bit input operands ----
1291 // or output values. ----
1292 // ----
1293 // out64 = intrinsic-node in64 ----
1294 // => ----
1295 // lo = copy (extract-element (in64, 0)) ----
1296 // hi = copy (extract-element (in64, 1)) ----
1297 // mips-specific-node ----
1298 // v0 = copy lo ----
1299 // v1 = copy hi ----
1300 // out64 = merge-values (v0, v1) ----
1301 // ----
1302 static SDValue lowerDSPIntr(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned Opc) { 0
1303 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
1304 bool HasChainIn = Op->getOperand(0).getValueType() == MVT::Other; 0
1305 SmallVector Ops; 0
1306 unsigned OpNo = 0; 0
1307 ----
1308 // See if Op has a chain input. ----
1309 if (HasChainIn) 0
1310 Ops.push_back(Op->getOperand(OpNo++)); 0
1311 ----
1312 // The next operand is the intrinsic opcode. ----
1313 assert(Op->getOperand(OpNo).getOpcode() == ISD::TargetConstant); 0
1314 ----
1315 // See if the next operand has type i64. ----
1316 SDValue Opnd = Op->getOperand(++OpNo), In64; 0
1317 ----
1318 if (Opnd.getValueType() == MVT::i64) 0
1319 In64 = initAccumulator(Opnd, DL, DAG); 0
1320 else ----
1321 Ops.push_back(Opnd); 0
1322 ----
1323 // Push the remaining operands. ----
1324 for (++OpNo ; OpNo < Op->getNumOperands(); ++OpNo) 0
1325 Ops.push_back(Op->getOperand(OpNo)); 0
1326 ----
1327 // Add In64 to the end of the list. ----
1328 if (In64.getNode()) 0
1329 Ops.push_back(In64); 0
1330 ----
1331 // Scan output. ----
1332 SmallVector ResTys; 0
1333 ----
1334 for (EVT Ty : Op->values()) 0
1335 ResTys.push_back((Ty == MVT::i64) ? MVT::Untyped : Ty); 0
1336 ----
1337 // Create node. ----
1338 SDValue Val = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, ResTys, Ops); 0
1339 SDValue Out = (ResTys[0] == MVT::Untyped) ? extractLOHI(Val, DL, DAG) : Val; 0
1340 ----
1341 if (!HasChainIn) 0
1342 return Out; 0
1343 ----
1344 assert(Val->getValueType(1) == MVT::Other); 0
1345 SDValue Vals[] = { Out, SDValue(Val.getNode(), 1) }; 0
1346 return DAG.getMergeValues(Vals, DL); 0
1347 } 0
1348 ----
1349 // Lower an MSA copy intrinsic into the specified SelectionDAG node ----
1350 static SDValue lowerMSACopyIntr(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned Opc) { 0
1351 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
1352 SDValue Vec = Op->getOperand(1); 0
1353 SDValue Idx = Op->getOperand(2); 0
1354 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
1355 EVT EltTy = Vec->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType(); 0
1356 ----
1357 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, ResTy, Vec, Idx, 0
1358 DAG.getValueType(EltTy)); ----
1359 ----
1360 return Result; 0
1361 } 0
1362 ----
1363 static SDValue lowerMSASplatZExt(SDValue Op, unsigned OpNr, SelectionDAG &DAG) { 0
1364 EVT ResVecTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
1365 EVT ViaVecTy = ResVecTy; 0
1366 bool BigEndian = !DAG.getSubtarget().getTargetTriple().isLittleEndian(); 0
1367 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
1368 ----
1369 // When ResVecTy == MVT::v2i64, LaneA is the upper 32 bits of the lane and ----
1370 // LaneB is the lower 32-bits. Otherwise LaneA and LaneB are alternating ----
1371 // lanes. ----
1372 SDValue LaneA = Op->getOperand(OpNr); 0
1373 SDValue LaneB; 0
1374 ----
1375 if (ResVecTy == MVT::v2i64) { 0
1376 // In case of the index being passed as an immediate value, set the upper ----
1377 // lane to 0 so that the splati.d instruction can be matched. ----
1378 if (isa(LaneA)) 0
1379 LaneB = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1380 // Having the index passed in a register, set the upper lane to the same ----
1381 // value as the lower - this results in the BUILD_VECTOR node not being ----
1382 // expanded through stack. This way we are able to pattern match the set of ----
1383 // nodes created here to splat.d. ----
1384 else ----
1385 LaneB = LaneA; 0
1386 ViaVecTy = MVT::v4i32; 0
1387 if(BigEndian) 0
1388 std::swap(LaneA, LaneB); 0
1389 } else ----
1390 LaneB = LaneA; 0
1391 ----
1392 SDValue Ops[16] = { LaneA, LaneB, LaneA, LaneB, LaneA, LaneB, LaneA, LaneB, ----
1393 LaneA, LaneB, LaneA, LaneB, LaneA, LaneB, LaneA, LaneB }; 0
1394 ----
1395 SDValue Result = DAG.getBuildVector( 0
1396 ViaVecTy, DL, ArrayRef(Ops, ViaVecTy.getVectorNumElements())); 0
1397 ----
1398 if (ViaVecTy != ResVecTy) { 0
1399 SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, ViaVecTy); 0
1400 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, ResVecTy, 0
1401 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ViaVecTy, Result, One)); ----
1402 } ----
1403 ----
1404 return Result; 0
1405 } 0
1406 ----
1407 static SDValue lowerMSASplatImm(SDValue Op, unsigned ImmOp, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
1408 bool IsSigned = false) { ----
1409 auto *CImm = cast(Op->getOperand(ImmOp)); 0
1410 return DAG.getConstant( 0
1411 APInt(Op->getValueType(0).getScalarType().getSizeInBits(), 0
1412 IsSigned ? CImm->getSExtValue() : CImm->getZExtValue(), IsSigned), 0
1413 SDLoc(Op), Op->getValueType(0)); 0
1414 } ----
1415 ----
1416 static SDValue getBuildVectorSplat(EVT VecTy, SDValue SplatValue, 0
1417 bool BigEndian, SelectionDAG &DAG) { ----
1418 EVT ViaVecTy = VecTy; 0
1419 SDValue SplatValueA = SplatValue; 0
1420 SDValue SplatValueB = SplatValue; 0
1421 SDLoc DL(SplatValue); 0
1422 ----
1423 if (VecTy == MVT::v2i64) { 0
1424 // v2i64 BUILD_VECTOR must be performed via v4i32 so split into i32's. ----
1425 ViaVecTy = MVT::v4i32; 0
1426 ----
1427 SplatValueA = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, SplatValue); 0
1428 SplatValueB = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i64, SplatValue, 0
1429 DAG.getConstant(32, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1430 SplatValueB = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, SplatValueB); 0
1431 } ----
1432 ----
1433 // We currently hold the parts in little endian order. Swap them if ----
1434 // necessary. ----
1435 if (BigEndian) 0
1436 std::swap(SplatValueA, SplatValueB); 0
1437 ----
1438 SDValue Ops[16] = { SplatValueA, SplatValueB, SplatValueA, SplatValueB, ----
1439 SplatValueA, SplatValueB, SplatValueA, SplatValueB, ----
1440 SplatValueA, SplatValueB, SplatValueA, SplatValueB, ----
1441 SplatValueA, SplatValueB, SplatValueA, SplatValueB }; 0
1442 ----
1443 SDValue Result = DAG.getBuildVector( 0
1444 ViaVecTy, DL, ArrayRef(Ops, ViaVecTy.getVectorNumElements())); 0
1445 ----
1446 if (VecTy != ViaVecTy) 0
1447 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VecTy, Result); 0
1448 ----
1449 return Result; 0
1450 } 0
1451 ----
1452 static SDValue lowerMSABinaryBitImmIntr(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
1453 unsigned Opc, SDValue Imm, ----
1454 bool BigEndian) { ----
1455 EVT VecTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
1456 SDValue Exp2Imm; 0
1457 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
1458 ----
1459 // The DAG Combiner can't constant fold bitcasted vectors yet so we must do it ----
1460 // here for now. ----
1461 if (VecTy == MVT::v2i64) { 0
1462 if (ConstantSDNode *CImm = dyn_cast(Imm)) { 0
1463 APInt BitImm = APInt(64, 1) << CImm->getAPIntValue(); 0
1464 ----
1465 SDValue BitImmHiOp = DAG.getConstant(BitImm.lshr(32).trunc(32), DL, 0
1466 MVT::i32); ----
1467 SDValue BitImmLoOp = DAG.getConstant(BitImm.trunc(32), DL, MVT::i32); 0
1468 ----
1469 if (BigEndian) 0
1470 std::swap(BitImmLoOp, BitImmHiOp); 0
1471 ----
1472 Exp2Imm = DAG.getNode( 0
1473 ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::v2i64, ----
1474 DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v4i32, DL, 0
1475 {BitImmLoOp, BitImmHiOp, BitImmLoOp, BitImmHiOp})); ----
1476 } 0
1477 } ----
1478 ----
1479 if (!Exp2Imm.getNode()) { 0
1480 // We couldnt constant fold, do a vector shift instead ----
1481 ----
1482 // Extend i32 to i64 if necessary. Sign or zero extend doesn't matter since ----
1483 // only values 0-63 are valid. ----
1484 if (VecTy == MVT::v2i64) 0
1485 Imm = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, Imm); 0
1486 ----
1487 Exp2Imm = getBuildVectorSplat(VecTy, Imm, BigEndian, DAG); 0
1488 ----
1489 Exp2Imm = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VecTy, DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VecTy), 0
1490 Exp2Imm); ----
1491 } ----
1492 ----
1493 return DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, VecTy, Op->getOperand(1), Exp2Imm); 0
1494 } 0
1495 ----
1496 static SDValue truncateVecElts(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) { 0
1497 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
1498 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
1499 SDValue Vec = Op->getOperand(2); 0
1500 bool BigEndian = !DAG.getSubtarget().getTargetTriple().isLittleEndian(); 0
1501 MVT ResEltTy = ResTy == MVT::v2i64 ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32; 0
1502 SDValue ConstValue = DAG.getConstant(Vec.getScalarValueSizeInBits() - 1, 0
1503 DL, ResEltTy); ----
1504 SDValue SplatVec = getBuildVectorSplat(ResTy, ConstValue, BigEndian, DAG); 0
1505 ----
1506 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ResTy, Vec, SplatVec); 0
1507 } 0
1508 ----
1509 static SDValue lowerMSABitClear(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) { 0
1510 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
1511 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
1512 SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, ResTy); 0
1513 SDValue Bit = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, ResTy, One, truncateVecElts(Op, DAG)); 0
1514 ----
1515 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ResTy, Op->getOperand(1), 0
1516 DAG.getNOT(DL, Bit, ResTy)); 0
1517 } 0
1518 ----
1519 static SDValue lowerMSABitClearImm(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) { 0
1520 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
1521 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
1522 APInt BitImm = APInt(ResTy.getScalarSizeInBits(), 1) 0
1523 << cast(Op->getOperand(2))->getAPIntValue(); 0
1524 SDValue BitMask = DAG.getConstant(~BitImm, DL, ResTy); 0
1525 ----
1526 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ResTy, Op->getOperand(1), BitMask); 0
1527 } 0
1528 ----
1529 SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerINTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN(SDValue Op, 0
1530 SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
1531 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
1532 unsigned Intrinsic = cast(Op->getOperand(0))->getZExtValue(); 0
1533 switch (Intrinsic) { 0
1534 default: 0
1535 return SDValue(); 0
1536 case Intrinsic::mips_shilo: 0
1537 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::SHILO); 0
1538 case Intrinsic::mips_dpau_h_qbl: 0
1539 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::DPAU_H_QBL); 0
1540 case Intrinsic::mips_dpau_h_qbr: 0
1541 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::DPAU_H_QBR); 0
1542 case Intrinsic::mips_dpsu_h_qbl: 0
1543 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::DPSU_H_QBL); 0
1544 case Intrinsic::mips_dpsu_h_qbr: 0
1545 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::DPSU_H_QBR); 0
1546 case Intrinsic::mips_dpa_w_ph: 0
1547 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::DPA_W_PH); 0
1548 case Intrinsic::mips_dps_w_ph: 0
1549 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::DPS_W_PH); 0
1550 case Intrinsic::mips_dpax_w_ph: 0
1551 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::DPAX_W_PH); 0
1552 case Intrinsic::mips_dpsx_w_ph: 0
1553 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::DPSX_W_PH); 0
1554 case Intrinsic::mips_mulsa_w_ph: 0
1555 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::MULSA_W_PH); 0
1556 case Intrinsic::mips_mult: 0
1557 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::Mult); 0
1558 case Intrinsic::mips_multu: 0
1559 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::Multu); 0
1560 case Intrinsic::mips_madd: 0
1561 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::MAdd); 0
1562 case Intrinsic::mips_maddu: 0
1563 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::MAddu); 0
1564 case Intrinsic::mips_msub: 0
1565 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::MSub); 0
1566 case Intrinsic::mips_msubu: 0
1567 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::MSubu); 0
1568 case Intrinsic::mips_addv_b: 0
1569 case Intrinsic::mips_addv_h: ----
1570 case Intrinsic::mips_addv_w: ----
1571 case Intrinsic::mips_addv_d: ----
1572 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1573 Op->getOperand(2)); 0
1574 case Intrinsic::mips_addvi_b: 0
1575 case Intrinsic::mips_addvi_h: ----
1576 case Intrinsic::mips_addvi_w: ----
1577 case Intrinsic::mips_addvi_d: ----
1578 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1579 lowerMSASplatImm(Op, 2, DAG)); 0
1580 case Intrinsic::mips_and_v: 0
1581 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1582 Op->getOperand(2)); 0
1583 case Intrinsic::mips_andi_b: 0
1584 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1585 lowerMSASplatImm(Op, 2, DAG)); 0
1586 case Intrinsic::mips_bclr_b: 0
1587 case Intrinsic::mips_bclr_h: ----
1588 case Intrinsic::mips_bclr_w: ----
1589 case Intrinsic::mips_bclr_d: ----
1590 return lowerMSABitClear(Op, DAG); 0
1591 case Intrinsic::mips_bclri_b: 0
1592 case Intrinsic::mips_bclri_h: ----
1593 case Intrinsic::mips_bclri_w: ----
1594 case Intrinsic::mips_bclri_d: ----
1595 return lowerMSABitClearImm(Op, DAG); 0
1596 case Intrinsic::mips_binsli_b: 0
1597 case Intrinsic::mips_binsli_h: ----
1598 case Intrinsic::mips_binsli_w: ----
1599 case Intrinsic::mips_binsli_d: { ----
1600 // binsli_x(IfClear, IfSet, nbits) -> (vselect LBitsMask, IfSet, IfClear) ----
1601 EVT VecTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
1602 EVT EltTy = VecTy.getVectorElementType(); 0
1603 if (Op->getConstantOperandVal(3) >= EltTy.getSizeInBits()) 0
1604 report_fatal_error("Immediate out of range"); 0
1605 APInt Mask = APInt::getHighBitsSet(EltTy.getSizeInBits(), 0
1606 Op->getConstantOperandVal(3) + 1); 0
1607 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, VecTy, 0
1608 DAG.getConstant(Mask, DL, VecTy, true), ----
1609 Op->getOperand(2), Op->getOperand(1)); 0
1610 } 0
1611 case Intrinsic::mips_binsri_b: 0
1612 case Intrinsic::mips_binsri_h: ----
1613 case Intrinsic::mips_binsri_w: ----
1614 case Intrinsic::mips_binsri_d: { ----
1615 // binsri_x(IfClear, IfSet, nbits) -> (vselect RBitsMask, IfSet, IfClear) ----
1616 EVT VecTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
1617 EVT EltTy = VecTy.getVectorElementType(); 0
1618 if (Op->getConstantOperandVal(3) >= EltTy.getSizeInBits()) 0
1619 report_fatal_error("Immediate out of range"); 0
1620 APInt Mask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(EltTy.getSizeInBits(), 0
1621 Op->getConstantOperandVal(3) + 1); 0
1622 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, VecTy, 0
1623 DAG.getConstant(Mask, DL, VecTy, true), ----
1624 Op->getOperand(2), Op->getOperand(1)); 0
1625 } 0
1626 case Intrinsic::mips_bmnz_v: 0
1627 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(3), 0
1628 Op->getOperand(2), Op->getOperand(1)); 0
1629 case Intrinsic::mips_bmnzi_b: 0
1630 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, Op->getValueType(0), 0
1631 lowerMSASplatImm(Op, 3, DAG), Op->getOperand(2), 0
1632 Op->getOperand(1)); 0
1633 case Intrinsic::mips_bmz_v: 0
1634 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(3), 0
1635 Op->getOperand(1), Op->getOperand(2)); 0
1636 case Intrinsic::mips_bmzi_b: 0
1637 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, Op->getValueType(0), 0
1638 lowerMSASplatImm(Op, 3, DAG), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1639 Op->getOperand(2)); 0
1640 case Intrinsic::mips_bneg_b: 0
1641 case Intrinsic::mips_bneg_h: ----
1642 case Intrinsic::mips_bneg_w: ----
1643 case Intrinsic::mips_bneg_d: { ----
1644 EVT VecTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
1645 SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VecTy); 0
1646 ----
1647 return DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, VecTy, Op->getOperand(1), 0
1648 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VecTy, One, ----
1649 truncateVecElts(Op, DAG))); 0
1650 } ----
1651 case Intrinsic::mips_bnegi_b: 0
1652 case Intrinsic::mips_bnegi_h: ----
1653 case Intrinsic::mips_bnegi_w: ----
1654 case Intrinsic::mips_bnegi_d: ----
1655 return lowerMSABinaryBitImmIntr(Op, DAG, ISD::XOR, Op->getOperand(2), 0
1656 !Subtarget.isLittle()); 0
1657 case Intrinsic::mips_bnz_b: 0
1658 case Intrinsic::mips_bnz_h: ----
1659 case Intrinsic::mips_bnz_w: ----
1660 case Intrinsic::mips_bnz_d: ----
1661 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VALL_NONZERO, DL, Op->getValueType(0), 0
1662 Op->getOperand(1)); 0
1663 case Intrinsic::mips_bnz_v: 0
1664 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VANY_NONZERO, DL, Op->getValueType(0), 0
1665 Op->getOperand(1)); 0
1666 case Intrinsic::mips_bsel_v: 0
1667 // bsel_v(Mask, IfClear, IfSet) -> (vselect Mask, IfSet, IfClear) ----
1668 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, Op->getValueType(0), 0
1669 Op->getOperand(1), Op->getOperand(3), 0
1670 Op->getOperand(2)); 0
1671 case Intrinsic::mips_bseli_b: 0
1672 // bseli_v(Mask, IfClear, IfSet) -> (vselect Mask, IfSet, IfClear) ----
1673 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, Op->getValueType(0), 0
1674 Op->getOperand(1), lowerMSASplatImm(Op, 3, DAG), 0
1675 Op->getOperand(2)); 0
1676 case Intrinsic::mips_bset_b: 0
1677 case Intrinsic::mips_bset_h: ----
1678 case Intrinsic::mips_bset_w: ----
1679 case Intrinsic::mips_bset_d: { ----
1680 EVT VecTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
1681 SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VecTy); 0
1682 ----
1683 return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VecTy, Op->getOperand(1), 0
1684 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VecTy, One, ----
1685 truncateVecElts(Op, DAG))); 0
1686 } ----
1687 case Intrinsic::mips_bseti_b: 0
1688 case Intrinsic::mips_bseti_h: ----
1689 case Intrinsic::mips_bseti_w: ----
1690 case Intrinsic::mips_bseti_d: ----
1691 return lowerMSABinaryBitImmIntr(Op, DAG, ISD::OR, Op->getOperand(2), 0
1692 !Subtarget.isLittle()); 0
1693 case Intrinsic::mips_bz_b: 0
1694 case Intrinsic::mips_bz_h: ----
1695 case Intrinsic::mips_bz_w: ----
1696 case Intrinsic::mips_bz_d: ----
1697 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VALL_ZERO, DL, Op->getValueType(0), 0
1698 Op->getOperand(1)); 0
1699 case Intrinsic::mips_bz_v: 0
1700 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VANY_ZERO, DL, Op->getValueType(0), 0
1701 Op->getOperand(1)); 0
1702 case Intrinsic::mips_ceq_b: 0
1703 case Intrinsic::mips_ceq_h: ----
1704 case Intrinsic::mips_ceq_w: ----
1705 case Intrinsic::mips_ceq_d: ----
1706 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1707 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETEQ); 0
1708 case Intrinsic::mips_ceqi_b: 0
1709 case Intrinsic::mips_ceqi_h: ----
1710 case Intrinsic::mips_ceqi_w: ----
1711 case Intrinsic::mips_ceqi_d: ----
1712 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1713 lowerMSASplatImm(Op, 2, DAG, true), ISD::SETEQ); 0
1714 case Intrinsic::mips_cle_s_b: 0
1715 case Intrinsic::mips_cle_s_h: ----
1716 case Intrinsic::mips_cle_s_w: ----
1717 case Intrinsic::mips_cle_s_d: ----
1718 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1719 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETLE); 0
1720 case Intrinsic::mips_clei_s_b: 0
1721 case Intrinsic::mips_clei_s_h: ----
1722 case Intrinsic::mips_clei_s_w: ----
1723 case Intrinsic::mips_clei_s_d: ----
1724 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1725 lowerMSASplatImm(Op, 2, DAG, true), ISD::SETLE); 0
1726 case Intrinsic::mips_cle_u_b: 0
1727 case Intrinsic::mips_cle_u_h: ----
1728 case Intrinsic::mips_cle_u_w: ----
1729 case Intrinsic::mips_cle_u_d: ----
1730 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1731 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETULE); 0
1732 case Intrinsic::mips_clei_u_b: 0
1733 case Intrinsic::mips_clei_u_h: ----
1734 case Intrinsic::mips_clei_u_w: ----
1735 case Intrinsic::mips_clei_u_d: ----
1736 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1737 lowerMSASplatImm(Op, 2, DAG), ISD::SETULE); 0
1738 case Intrinsic::mips_clt_s_b: 0
1739 case Intrinsic::mips_clt_s_h: ----
1740 case Intrinsic::mips_clt_s_w: ----
1741 case Intrinsic::mips_clt_s_d: ----
1742 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1743 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETLT); 0
1744 case Intrinsic::mips_clti_s_b: 0
1745 case Intrinsic::mips_clti_s_h: ----
1746 case Intrinsic::mips_clti_s_w: ----
1747 case Intrinsic::mips_clti_s_d: ----
1748 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1749 lowerMSASplatImm(Op, 2, DAG, true), ISD::SETLT); 0
1750 case Intrinsic::mips_clt_u_b: 0
1751 case Intrinsic::mips_clt_u_h: ----
1752 case Intrinsic::mips_clt_u_w: ----
1753 case Intrinsic::mips_clt_u_d: ----
1754 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1755 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETULT); 0
1756 case Intrinsic::mips_clti_u_b: 0
1757 case Intrinsic::mips_clti_u_h: ----
1758 case Intrinsic::mips_clti_u_w: ----
1759 case Intrinsic::mips_clti_u_d: ----
1760 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1761 lowerMSASplatImm(Op, 2, DAG), ISD::SETULT); 0
1762 case Intrinsic::mips_copy_s_b: 0
1763 case Intrinsic::mips_copy_s_h: ----
1764 case Intrinsic::mips_copy_s_w: ----
1765 return lowerMSACopyIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT); 0
1766 case Intrinsic::mips_copy_s_d: 0
1767 if (Subtarget.hasMips64()) 0
1768 // Lower directly into VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT since i64 is legal on Mips64. ----
1769 return lowerMSACopyIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT); 0
1770 else { ----
1771 // Lower into the generic EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT node and let the type ----
1772 // legalizer and EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT lowering sort it out. ----
1773 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SDLoc(Op), 0
1774 Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1775 Op->getOperand(2)); 0
1776 } ----
1777 case Intrinsic::mips_copy_u_b: 0
1778 case Intrinsic::mips_copy_u_h: ----
1779 case Intrinsic::mips_copy_u_w: ----
1780 return lowerMSACopyIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::VEXTRACT_ZEXT_ELT); 0
1781 case Intrinsic::mips_copy_u_d: 0
1782 if (Subtarget.hasMips64()) 0
1783 // Lower directly into VEXTRACT_ZEXT_ELT since i64 is legal on Mips64. ----
1784 return lowerMSACopyIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::VEXTRACT_ZEXT_ELT); 0
1785 else { ----
1786 // Lower into the generic EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT node and let the type ----
1787 // legalizer and EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT lowering sort it out. ----
1788 // Note: When i64 is illegal, this results in copy_s.w instructions ----
1789 // instead of copy_u.w instructions. This makes no difference to the ----
1790 // behaviour since i64 is only illegal when the register file is 32-bit. ----
1791 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SDLoc(Op), 0
1792 Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1793 Op->getOperand(2)); 0
1794 } ----
1795 case Intrinsic::mips_div_s_b: 0
1796 case Intrinsic::mips_div_s_h: ----
1797 case Intrinsic::mips_div_s_w: ----
1798 case Intrinsic::mips_div_s_d: ----
1799 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SDIV, DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1800 Op->getOperand(2)); 0
1801 case Intrinsic::mips_div_u_b: 0
1802 case Intrinsic::mips_div_u_h: ----
1803 case Intrinsic::mips_div_u_w: ----
1804 case Intrinsic::mips_div_u_d: ----
1805 return DAG.getNode(ISD::UDIV, DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1806 Op->getOperand(2)); 0
1807 case Intrinsic::mips_fadd_w: 0
1808 case Intrinsic::mips_fadd_d: ----
1809 // TODO: If intrinsics have fast-math-flags, propagate them. ----
1810 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FADD, DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1811 Op->getOperand(2)); 0
1812 // Don't lower mips_fcaf_[wd] since LLVM folds SETFALSE condcodes away ----
1813 case Intrinsic::mips_fceq_w: 0
1814 case Intrinsic::mips_fceq_d: ----
1815 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1816 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETOEQ); 0
1817 case Intrinsic::mips_fcle_w: 0
1818 case Intrinsic::mips_fcle_d: ----
1819 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1820 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETOLE); 0
1821 case Intrinsic::mips_fclt_w: 0
1822 case Intrinsic::mips_fclt_d: ----
1823 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1824 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETOLT); 0
1825 case Intrinsic::mips_fcne_w: 0
1826 case Intrinsic::mips_fcne_d: ----
1827 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1828 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETONE); 0
1829 case Intrinsic::mips_fcor_w: 0
1830 case Intrinsic::mips_fcor_d: ----
1831 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1832 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETO); 0
1833 case Intrinsic::mips_fcueq_w: 0
1834 case Intrinsic::mips_fcueq_d: ----
1835 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1836 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETUEQ); 0
1837 case Intrinsic::mips_fcule_w: 0
1838 case Intrinsic::mips_fcule_d: ----
1839 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1840 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETULE); 0
1841 case Intrinsic::mips_fcult_w: 0
1842 case Intrinsic::mips_fcult_d: ----
1843 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1844 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETULT); 0
1845 case Intrinsic::mips_fcun_w: 0
1846 case Intrinsic::mips_fcun_d: ----
1847 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1848 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETUO); 0
1849 case Intrinsic::mips_fcune_w: 0
1850 case Intrinsic::mips_fcune_d: ----
1851 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1852 Op->getOperand(2), ISD::SETUNE); 0
1853 case Intrinsic::mips_fdiv_w: 0
1854 case Intrinsic::mips_fdiv_d: ----
1855 // TODO: If intrinsics have fast-math-flags, propagate them. ----
1856 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FDIV, DL, Op->getValueType(0), Op->getOperand(1), 0
1857 Op->getOperand(2)); 0
1858 case Intrinsic::mips_ffint_u_w: 0

2281 ----
2282 static SDValue lowerMSALoadIntr(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned Intr, 0
2283 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
2284 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2285 SDValue ChainIn = Op->getOperand(0); 0
2286 SDValue Address = Op->getOperand(2); 0

2391 // Lower ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT into MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT. ----
2392 // ----
2393 // The non-value bits resulting from ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT are undefined. We ----
2394 // choose to sign-extend but we could have equally chosen zero-extend. The ----
2395 // DAGCombiner will fold any sign/zero extension of the ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT ----
2396 // result into this node later (possibly changing it to a zero-extend in the ----
2397 // process). ----
2398 SDValue MipsSETargetLowering:: 0
2399 lowerEXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
2400 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2401 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
2402 SDValue Op0 = Op->getOperand(0); 0
2403 EVT VecTy = Op0->getValueType(0); 0
2404 ----
2405 if (!VecTy.is128BitVector()) 0
2406 return SDValue(); 0
2407 ----
2408 if (ResTy.isInteger()) { 0
2409 SDValue Op1 = Op->getOperand(1); 0
2410 EVT EltTy = VecTy.getVectorElementType(); 0
2411 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT, DL, ResTy, Op0, Op1, 0
2412 DAG.getValueType(EltTy)); 0
2413 } ----
2414 ----
2415 return Op; 0
2416 } 0
2417 ----
2418 static bool isConstantOrUndef(const SDValue Op) { 0
2419 if (Op->isUndef()) 0
2420 return true; 0
2421 if (isa(Op)) 0
2422 return true; 0
2423 if (isa(Op)) 0
2424 return true; 0
2425 return false; 0
2426 } ----
2427 ----
2428 static bool isConstantOrUndefBUILD_VECTOR(const BuildVectorSDNode *Op) { 0
2429 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Op->getNumOperands(); ++i) 0
2430 if (isConstantOrUndef(Op->getOperand(i))) 0
2431 return true; 0
2432 return false; 0
2433 } ----
2434 ----
2435 // Lowers ISD::BUILD_VECTOR into appropriate SelectionDAG nodes for the ----
2436 // backend. ----
2437 // ----
2438 // Lowers according to the following rules: ----
2439 // - Constant splats are legal as-is as long as the SplatBitSize is a power of ----
2440 // 2 less than or equal to 64 and the value fits into a signed 10-bit ----
2441 // immediate ----
2442 // - Constant splats are lowered to bitconverted BUILD_VECTORs if SplatBitSize ----
2443 // is a power of 2 less than or equal to 64 and the value does not fit into a ----
2444 // signed 10-bit immediate ----
2445 // - Non-constant splats are legal as-is. ----
2446 // - Non-constant non-splats are lowered to sequences of INSERT_VECTOR_ELT. ----
2447 // - All others are illegal and must be expanded. ----
2448 SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerBUILD_VECTOR(SDValue Op, 0
2449 SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
2450 BuildVectorSDNode *Node = cast(Op); 0
2451 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
2452 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2453 APInt SplatValue, SplatUndef; 0
2454 unsigned SplatBitSize; ----
2455 bool HasAnyUndefs; ----
2456 ----
2457 if (!Subtarget.hasMSA() || !ResTy.is128BitVector()) 0
2458 return SDValue(); 0
2459 ----
2460 if (Node->isConstantSplat(SplatValue, SplatUndef, SplatBitSize, 0
2461 HasAnyUndefs, 8, ----
2462 !Subtarget.isLittle()) && SplatBitSize <= 64) { 0
2463 // We can only cope with 8, 16, 32, or 64-bit elements ----
2464 if (SplatBitSize != 8 && SplatBitSize != 16 && SplatBitSize != 32 && 0
2465 SplatBitSize != 64) 0
2466 return SDValue(); 0
2467 ----
2468 // If the value isn't an integer type we will have to bitcast ----
2469 // from an integer type first. Also, if there are any undefs, we must ----
2470 // lower them to defined values first. ----
2471 if (ResTy.isInteger() && !HasAnyUndefs) 0
2472 return Op; 0
2473 ----
2474 EVT ViaVecTy; 0
2475 ----
2476 switch (SplatBitSize) { 0
2477 default: 0
2478 return SDValue(); 0
2479 case 8: 0
2480 ViaVecTy = MVT::v16i8; 0
2481 break; 0
2482 case 16: 0
2483 ViaVecTy = MVT::v8i16; 0
2484 break; 0
2485 case 32: 0
2486 ViaVecTy = MVT::v4i32; 0
2487 break; 0
2488 case 64: 0
2489 // There's no fill.d to fall back on for 64-bit values ----
2490 return SDValue(); 0
2491 } ----
2492 ----
2493 // SelectionDAG::getConstant will promote SplatValue appropriately. ----
2494 SDValue Result = DAG.getConstant(SplatValue, DL, ViaVecTy); 0
2495 ----
2496 // Bitcast to the type we originally wanted ----
2497 if (ViaVecTy != ResTy) 0
2498 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SDLoc(Node), ResTy, Result); 0
2499 ----
2500 return Result; 0
2501 } else if (DAG.isSplatValue(Op, /* AllowUndefs */ false)) 0
2502 return Op; 0
2503 else if (!isConstantOrUndefBUILD_VECTOR(Node)) { 0
2504 // Use INSERT_VECTOR_ELT operations rather than expand to stores. ----
2505 // The resulting code is the same length as the expansion, but it doesn't ----
2506 // use memory operations ----
2507 EVT ResTy = Node->getValueType(0); 0
2508 ----
2509 assert(ResTy.isVector()); 0
2510 ----
2511 unsigned NumElts = ResTy.getVectorNumElements(); 0
2512 SDValue Vector = DAG.getUNDEF(ResTy); 0
2513 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElts; ++i) { 0
2514 Vector = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, ResTy, Vector, 0
2515 Node->getOperand(i), 0
2516 DAG.getConstant(i, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2517 } ----
2518 return Vector; 0
2519 } ----
2520 ----
2521 return SDValue(); 0
2522 } 0
2523 ----
2524 // Lower VECTOR_SHUFFLE into SHF (if possible). ----
2525 // ----
2526 // SHF splits the vector into blocks of four elements, then shuffles these ----
2527 // elements according to a <4 x i2> constant (encoded as an integer immediate). ----
2528 // ----
2529 // It is therefore possible to lower into SHF when the mask takes the form: ----
2530 // ----
2531 // When undef's appear they are treated as if they were whatever value is ----
2532 // necessary in order to fit the above forms. ----
2533 // ----
2534 // For example: ----
2535 // %2 = shufflevector <8 x i16> %0, <8 x i16> undef, ----
2536 // <8 x i32> ----
2537 // i32 7, i32 6, i32 5, i32 4> ----
2538 // is lowered to: ----
2539 // (SHF_H $w0, $w1, 27) ----
2540 // where the 27 comes from: ----
2541 // 3 + (2 << 2) + (1 << 4) + (0 << 6) ----
2542 static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_SHF(SDValue Op, EVT ResTy, 0
2543 SmallVector Indices, ----
2544 SelectionDAG &DAG) { ----
2545 int SHFIndices[4] = { -1, -1, -1, -1 }; 0
2546 ----
2547 if (Indices.size() < 4) 0
2548 return SDValue(); 0
2549 ----
2550 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 4; ++i) { 0
2551 for (unsigned j = i; j < Indices.size(); j += 4) { 0
2552 int Idx = Indices[j]; 0
2553 ----
2554 // Convert from vector index to 4-element subvector index ----
2555 // If an index refers to an element outside of the subvector then give up ----
2556 if (Idx != -1) { 0
2557 Idx -= 4 * (j / 4); 0
2558 if (Idx < 0 || Idx >= 4) 0
2559 return SDValue(); 0
2560 } ----
2561 ----
2562 // If the mask has an undef, replace it with the current index. ----
2563 // Note that it might still be undef if the current index is also undef ----
2564 if (SHFIndices[i] == -1) 0
2565 SHFIndices[i] = Idx; 0
2566 ----
2567 // Check that non-undef values are the same as in the mask. If they ----
2568 // aren't then give up ----
2569 if (!(Idx == -1 || Idx == SHFIndices[i])) 0
2570 return SDValue(); 0
2571 } ----
2572 } ----
2573 ----
2574 // Calculate the immediate. Replace any remaining undefs with zero ----
2575 APInt Imm(32, 0); 0
2576 for (int i = 3; i >= 0; --i) { 0
2577 int Idx = SHFIndices[i]; 0
2578 ----
2579 if (Idx == -1) 0
2580 Idx = 0; 0
2581 ----
2582 Imm <<= 2; 0
2583 Imm |= Idx & 0x3; 0
2584 } ----
2585 ----
2586 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2587 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::SHF, DL, ResTy, 0
2588 DAG.getTargetConstant(Imm, DL, MVT::i32), 0
2589 Op->getOperand(0)); 0
2590 } 0

2592 /// Determine whether a range fits a regular pattern of values. ----
2593 /// This function accounts for the possibility of jumping over the End iterator. ----
2594 template ----
2595 static bool ----
2596 fitsRegularPattern(typename SmallVectorImpl::const_iterator Begin, 0
2597 unsigned CheckStride, ----
2598 typename SmallVectorImpl::const_iterator End, ----
2599 ValType ExpectedIndex, unsigned ExpectedIndexStride) { ----
2600 auto &I = Begin; 0
2601 ----
2602 while (I != End) { 0
2603 if (*I != -1 && *I != ExpectedIndex) 0
2604 return false; 0
2605 ExpectedIndex += ExpectedIndexStride; 0
2606 ----
2607 // Incrementing past End is undefined behaviour so we must increment one ----
2608 // step at a time and check for End at each step. ----
2609 for (unsigned n = 0; n < CheckStride && I != End; ++n, ++I) 0
2610 ; // Empty loop body. ----
2611 } ----
2612 return true; 0
2613 } ----
2614 ----
2615 // Determine whether VECTOR_SHUFFLE is a SPLATI. ----
2616 // ----
2617 // It is a SPLATI when the mask is: ----
2618 // ----
2619 // where x is any valid index. ----
2620 // ----
2621 // When undef's appear in the mask they are treated as if they were whatever ----
2622 // value is necessary in order to fit the above form. ----
2623 static bool isVECTOR_SHUFFLE_SPLATI(SDValue Op, EVT ResTy, 0
2624 SmallVector Indices, ----
2625 SelectionDAG &DAG) { ----
2626 assert((Indices.size() % 2) == 0); 0
2627 ----
2628 int SplatIndex = -1; 0
2629 for (const auto &V : Indices) { 0
2630 if (V != -1) { 0
2631 SplatIndex = V; 0
2632 break; 0
2633 } ----
2634 } ----
2635 ----
2636 return fitsRegularPattern(Indices.begin(), 1, Indices.end(), SplatIndex, 0
2637 0); 0
2638 } ----
2639 ----
2640 // Lower VECTOR_SHUFFLE into ILVEV (if possible). ----
2641 // ----
2642 // ILVEV interleaves the even elements from each vector. ----
2643 // ----
2644 // It is possible to lower into ILVEV when the mask consists of two of the ----
2645 // following forms interleaved: ----
2646 // <0, 2, 4, ...> ----
2647 // ----
2648 // where n is the number of elements in the vector. ----
2649 // For example: ----
2650 // <0, 0, 2, 2, 4, 4, ...> ----
2651 // <0, n, 2, n+2, 4, n+4, ...> ----
2652 // ----
2653 // When undef's appear in the mask they are treated as if they were whatever ----
2654 // value is necessary in order to fit the above forms. ----
2655 static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_ILVEV(SDValue Op, EVT ResTy, 0
2656 SmallVector Indices, ----
2657 SelectionDAG &DAG) { ----
2658 assert((Indices.size() % 2) == 0); 0
2659 ----
2660 SDValue Wt; 0
2661 SDValue Ws; 0
2662 const auto &Begin = Indices.begin(); 0
2663 const auto &End = Indices.end(); 0
2664 ----
2665 // Check even elements are taken from the even elements of one half or the ----
2666 // other and pick an operand accordingly. ----
2667 if (fitsRegularPattern(Begin, 2, End, 0, 2)) 0
2668 Wt = Op->getOperand(0); 0
2669 else if (fitsRegularPattern(Begin, 2, End, Indices.size(), 2)) 0
2670 Wt = Op->getOperand(1); 0
2671 else ----
2672 return SDValue(); 0
2673 ----
2674 // Check odd elements are taken from the even elements of one half or the ----
2675 // other and pick an operand accordingly. ----
2676 if (fitsRegularPattern(Begin + 1, 2, End, 0, 2)) 0
2677 Ws = Op->getOperand(0); 0
2678 else if (fitsRegularPattern(Begin + 1, 2, End, Indices.size(), 2)) 0
2679 Ws = Op->getOperand(1); 0
2680 else ----
2681 return SDValue(); 0
2682 ----
2683 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ILVEV, SDLoc(Op), ResTy, Ws, Wt); 0
2684 } ----

2691 // following forms interleaved: ----

2759 // one half or the other and pick an operand accordingly. ----

2782 // of each vector. ----
2783 // ----
2784 // It is possible to lower into ILVL when the mask consists of two of the ----
2785 // following forms interleaved: ----
2786 // ----
2787 // ----
2788 // where n is the number of elements in the vector and x is half n. ----
2789 // For example: ----
2790 // ----
2791 // ----

2793 // When undef's appear in the mask they are treated as if they were whatever ----
2794 // value is necessary in order to fit the above forms. ----
2795 static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_ILVL(SDValue Op, EVT ResTy, 0
2796 SmallVector Indices, ----
2797 SelectionDAG &DAG) { ----
2798 assert((Indices.size() % 2) == 0); 0
2799 ----
2800 unsigned HalfSize = Indices.size() / 2; 0
2801 SDValue Wt; 0
2802 SDValue Ws; 0
2803 const auto &Begin = Indices.begin(); 0
2804 const auto &End = Indices.end(); 0
2805 ----
2806 // Check even elements are taken from the left (highest-indexed) elements of ----
2807 // one half or the other and pick an operand accordingly. ----
2808 if (fitsRegularPattern(Begin, 2, End, HalfSize, 1)) 0
2809 Wt = Op->getOperand(0); 0
2810 else if (fitsRegularPattern(Begin, 2, End, Indices.size() + HalfSize, 1)) 0
2811 Wt = Op->getOperand(1); 0
2812 else ----
2813 return SDValue(); 0
2814 ----
2815 // Check odd elements are taken from the left (highest-indexed) elements of ----
2816 // one half or the other and pick an operand accordingly. ----
2817 if (fitsRegularPattern(Begin + 1, 2, End, HalfSize, 1)) 0
2818 Ws = Op->getOperand(0); 0
2819 else if (fitsRegularPattern(Begin + 1, 2, End, Indices.size() + HalfSize, 0
2820 1)) ----
2821 Ws = Op->getOperand(1); 0
2822 else ----
2823 return SDValue(); 0
2824 ----
2825 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ILVL, SDLoc(Op), ResTy, Ws, Wt); 0

2827 ----
2828 // Lower VECTOR_SHUFFLE into PCKEV (if possible). ----
2829 // ----
2830 // PCKEV copies the even elements of each vector into the result vector. ----
2831 // ----
2832 // It is possible to lower into PCKEV when the mask consists of two of the ----
2833 // following forms concatenated: ----
2834 // <0, 2, 4, ...> ----
2835 // ----
2836 // where n is the number of elements in the vector. ----
2837 // For example: ----
2838 // <0, 2, 4, ..., 0, 2, 4, ...> ----
2839 // <0, 2, 4, ..., n, n+2, n+4, ...> ----
2840 // ----
2841 // When undef's appear in the mask they are treated as if they were whatever ----
2842 // value is necessary in order to fit the above forms. ----
2843 static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_PCKEV(SDValue Op, EVT ResTy, 0
2844 SmallVector Indices, ----
2845 SelectionDAG &DAG) { ----
2846 assert((Indices.size() % 2) == 0); 0
2847 ----
2848 SDValue Wt; 0
2849 SDValue Ws; 0
2850 const auto &Begin = Indices.begin(); 0
2851 const auto &Mid = Indices.begin() + Indices.size() / 2; 0
2852 const auto &End = Indices.end(); 0
2853 ----
2854 if (fitsRegularPattern(Begin, 1, Mid, 0, 2)) 0
2855 Wt = Op->getOperand(0); 0
2856 else if (fitsRegularPattern(Begin, 1, Mid, Indices.size(), 2)) 0
2857 Wt = Op->getOperand(1); 0
2858 else ----
2859 return SDValue(); 0
2860 ----
2861 if (fitsRegularPattern(Mid, 1, End, 0, 2)) 0
2862 Ws = Op->getOperand(0); 0
2863 else if (fitsRegularPattern(Mid, 1, End, Indices.size(), 2)) 0
2864 Ws = Op->getOperand(1); 0
2865 else ----
2866 return SDValue(); 0
2867 ----
2868 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::PCKEV, SDLoc(Op), ResTy, Ws, Wt); 0
2869 } ----
2870 ----
2871 // Lower VECTOR_SHUFFLE into PCKOD (if possible). ----
2872 // ----
2873 // PCKOD copies the odd elements of each vector into the result vector. ----
2874 // ----
2875 // It is possible to lower into PCKOD when the mask consists of two of the ----
2876 // following forms concatenated: ----
2877 // <1, 3, 5, ...> ----
2878 // ----
2879 // where n is the number of elements in the vector. ----
2880 // For example: ----
2881 // <1, 3, 5, ..., 1, 3, 5, ...> ----
2882 // <1, 3, 5, ..., n+1, n+3, n+5, ...> ----
2883 // ----
2884 // When undef's appear in the mask they are treated as if they were whatever ----
2885 // value is necessary in order to fit the above forms. ----
2886 static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_PCKOD(SDValue Op, EVT ResTy, 0
2887 SmallVector Indices, ----
2888 SelectionDAG &DAG) { ----
2889 assert((Indices.size() % 2) == 0); 0
2890 ----
2891 SDValue Wt; 0
2892 SDValue Ws; 0
2893 const auto &Begin = Indices.begin(); 0
2894 const auto &Mid = Indices.begin() + Indices.size() / 2; 0
2895 const auto &End = Indices.end(); 0
2896 ----
2897 if (fitsRegularPattern(Begin, 1, Mid, 1, 2)) 0
2898 Wt = Op->getOperand(0); 0
2899 else if (fitsRegularPattern(Begin, 1, Mid, Indices.size() + 1, 2)) 0
2900 Wt = Op->getOperand(1); 0
2901 else ----
2902 return SDValue(); 0
2903 ----
2904 if (fitsRegularPattern(Mid, 1, End, 1, 2)) 0
2905 Ws = Op->getOperand(0); 0
2906 else if (fitsRegularPattern(Mid, 1, End, Indices.size() + 1, 2)) 0
2907 Ws = Op->getOperand(1); 0
2908 else ----
2909 return SDValue(); 0
2910 ----
2911 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::PCKOD, SDLoc(Op), ResTy, Ws, Wt); 0
2912 } ----
2913 ----
2914 // Lower VECTOR_SHUFFLE into VSHF. ----
2915 // ----
2916 // This mostly consists of converting the shuffle indices in Indices into a ----
2917 // BUILD_VECTOR and adding it as an operand to the resulting VSHF. There is ----
2918 // also code to eliminate unused operands of the VECTOR_SHUFFLE. For example, ----
2919 // if the type is v8i16 and all the indices are less than 8 then the second ----
2920 // operand is unused and can be replaced with anything. We choose to replace it ----
2921 // with the used operand since this reduces the number of instructions overall. ----
2922 static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_VSHF(SDValue Op, EVT ResTy, 0
2923 const SmallVector &Indices, ----
2924 SelectionDAG &DAG) { ----
2925 SmallVector Ops; 0
2926 SDValue Op0; 0
2927 SDValue Op1; 0
2928 EVT MaskVecTy = ResTy.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger(); 0
2929 EVT MaskEltTy = MaskVecTy.getVectorElementType(); 0
2930 bool Using1stVec = false; 0
2931 bool Using2ndVec = false; 0
2932 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2933 int ResTyNumElts = ResTy.getVectorNumElements(); 0
2934 ----
2935 for (int i = 0; i < ResTyNumElts; ++i) { 0
2936 // Idx == -1 means UNDEF ----
2937 int Idx = Indices[i]; 0
2938 ----
2939 if (0 <= Idx && Idx < ResTyNumElts) 0
2940 Using1stVec = true; 0
2941 if (ResTyNumElts <= Idx && Idx < ResTyNumElts * 2) 0
2942 Using2ndVec = true; 0
2943 } ----
2944 ----
2945 for (int Idx : Indices) 0
2946 Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(Idx, DL, MaskEltTy)); 0
2947 ----
2948 SDValue MaskVec = DAG.getBuildVector(MaskVecTy, DL, Ops); 0
2949 ----
2950 if (Using1stVec && Using2ndVec) { 0
2951 Op0 = Op->getOperand(0); 0
2952 Op1 = Op->getOperand(1); 0
2953 } else if (Using1stVec) 0
2954 Op0 = Op1 = Op->getOperand(0); 0
2955 else if (Using2ndVec) 0
2956 Op0 = Op1 = Op->getOperand(1); 0
2957 else ----
2958 llvm_unreachable("shuffle vector mask references neither vector operand?"); 0
2959 ----
2960 // VECTOR_SHUFFLE concatenates the vectors in an vectorwise fashion. ----
2961 // <0b00, 0b01> + <0b10, 0b11> -> <0b00, 0b01, 0b10, 0b11> ----
2962 // VSHF concatenates the vectors in a bitwise fashion: ----
2963 // <0b00, 0b01> + <0b10, 0b11> -> ----
2964 // 0b0100 + 0b1110 -> 0b01001110 ----
2965 // <0b10, 0b11, 0b00, 0b01> ----
2966 // We must therefore swap the operands to get the correct result. ----
2967 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VSHF, DL, ResTy, MaskVec, Op1, Op0); 0
2968 } 0
2969 ----
2970 // Lower VECTOR_SHUFFLE into one of a number of instructions depending on the ----
2971 // indices in the shuffle. ----
2972 SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE(SDValue Op, 0
2973 SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
2974 ShuffleVectorSDNode *Node = cast(Op); 0
2975 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0); 0
2976 ----
2977 if (!ResTy.is128BitVector()) 0
2978 return SDValue(); 0
2979 ----
2980 int ResTyNumElts = ResTy.getVectorNumElements(); 0
2981 SmallVector Indices; 0
2982 ----
2983 for (int i = 0; i < ResTyNumElts; ++i) 0
2984 Indices.push_back(Node->getMaskElt(i)); 0
2985 ----
2986 // splati.[bhwd] is preferable to the others but is matched from ----
2987 // MipsISD::VSHF. ----
2988 if (isVECTOR_SHUFFLE_SPLATI(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG)) 0
2989 return lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_VSHF(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG); 0
2990 SDValue Result; 0
2991 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_ILVEV(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG))) 0
2992 return Result; 0
2993 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_ILVOD(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG))) 0
2994 return Result; 0
2995 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_ILVL(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG))) 0
2996 return Result; 0
2997 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_ILVR(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG))) 0
2998 return Result; 0
2999 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_PCKEV(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG))) 0
3000 return Result; 0
3001 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_PCKOD(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG))) 0
3002 return Result; 0
3003 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_SHF(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG))) 0
3004 return Result; 0
3005 return lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_VSHF(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG); 0
3006 } 0
3007 ----
3008 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3009 MipsSETargetLowering::emitBPOSGE32(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3010 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
3011 // $bb: ----
3012 // bposge32_pseudo $vr0 ----
3013 // => ----
3014 // $bb: ----
3015 // bposge32 $tbb ----
3016 // $fbb: ----
3017 // li $vr2, 0 ----
3018 // b $sink ----
3019 // $tbb: ----
3020 // li $vr1, 1 ----
3021 // $sink: ----
3022 // $vr0 = phi($vr2, $fbb, $vr1, $tbb) ----
3023 ----
3024 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3025 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3026 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &Mips::GPR32RegClass; 0
3027 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3028 const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock(); 0
3029 MachineFunction::iterator It = std::next(MachineFunction::iterator(BB)); 0
3030 MachineFunction *F = BB->getParent(); 0
3031 MachineBasicBlock *FBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB); 0
3032 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB); 0
3033 MachineBasicBlock *Sink = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB); 0
3034 F->insert(It, FBB); 0
3035 F->insert(It, TBB); 0
3036 F->insert(It, Sink); 0
3037 ----
3038 // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to Sink. ----
3039 Sink->splice(Sink->begin(), BB, std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), 0
3040 BB->end()); ----
3041 Sink->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB); 0
3042 ----
3043 // Add successors. ----
3044 BB->addSuccessor(FBB); 0
3045 BB->addSuccessor(TBB); 0
3046 FBB->addSuccessor(Sink); 0
3047 TBB->addSuccessor(Sink); 0
3048 ----
3049 // Insert the real bposge32 instruction to $BB. ----
3050 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::BPOSGE32)).addMBB(TBB); 0
3051 // Insert the real bposge32c instruction to $BB. ----
3052 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::BPOSGE32C_MMR3)).addMBB(TBB); 0
3053 ----
3054 // Fill $FBB. ----
3055 Register VR2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
3056 BuildMI(*FBB, FBB->end(), DL, TII->get(Mips::ADDiu), VR2) 0
3057 .addReg(Mips::ZERO).addImm(0); 0
3058 BuildMI(*FBB, FBB->end(), DL, TII->get(Mips::B)).addMBB(Sink); 0
3059 ----
3060 // Fill $TBB. ----
3061 Register VR1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
3062 BuildMI(*TBB, TBB->end(), DL, TII->get(Mips::ADDiu), VR1) 0
3063 .addReg(Mips::ZERO).addImm(1); 0
3064 ----
3065 // Insert phi function to $Sink. ----
3066 BuildMI(*Sink, Sink->begin(), DL, TII->get(Mips::PHI), 0
3067 MI.getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
3068 .addReg(VR2) 0
3069 .addMBB(FBB) 0
3070 .addReg(VR1) 0
3071 .addMBB(TBB); 0
3072 ----
3073 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now. 0
3074 return Sink; 0
3075 } 0
3076 ----
3077 MachineBasicBlock *MipsSETargetLowering::emitMSACBranchPseudo( 0
3078 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB, unsigned BranchOp) const { ----
3079 // $bb: ----
3080 // vany_nonzero $rd, $ws ----
3081 // => ----
3082 // $bb: ----
3083 // bnz.b $ws, $tbb ----
3084 // b $fbb ----
3085 // $fbb: ----
3086 // li $rd1, 0 ----
3087 // b $sink ----
3088 // $tbb: ----
3089 // li $rd2, 1 ----
3090 // $sink: ----
3091 // $rd = phi($rd1, $fbb, $rd2, $tbb) ----
3092 ----
3093 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3094 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3095 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &Mips::GPR32RegClass; 0
3096 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3097 const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock(); 0
3098 MachineFunction::iterator It = std::next(MachineFunction::iterator(BB)); 0
3099 MachineFunction *F = BB->getParent(); 0
3100 MachineBasicBlock *FBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB); 0
3101 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB); 0
3102 MachineBasicBlock *Sink = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB); 0
3103 F->insert(It, FBB); 0
3104 F->insert(It, TBB); 0
3105 F->insert(It, Sink); 0
3106 ----
3107 // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to Sink. ----
3108 Sink->splice(Sink->begin(), BB, std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), 0
3109 BB->end()); ----
3110 Sink->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB); 0
3111 ----
3112 // Add successors. ----
3113 BB->addSuccessor(FBB); 0
3114 BB->addSuccessor(TBB); 0
3115 FBB->addSuccessor(Sink); 0
3116 TBB->addSuccessor(Sink); 0
3117 ----
3118 // Insert the real bnz.b instruction to $BB. ----
3119 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(BranchOp)) 0
3120 .addReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
3121 .addMBB(TBB); 0
3122 ----
3123 // Fill $FBB. ----
3124 Register RD1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
3125 BuildMI(*FBB, FBB->end(), DL, TII->get(Mips::ADDiu), RD1) 0
3126 .addReg(Mips::ZERO).addImm(0); 0
3127 BuildMI(*FBB, FBB->end(), DL, TII->get(Mips::B)).addMBB(Sink); 0
3128 ----
3129 // Fill $TBB. ----
3130 Register RD2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
3131 BuildMI(*TBB, TBB->end(), DL, TII->get(Mips::ADDiu), RD2) 0
3132 .addReg(Mips::ZERO).addImm(1); 0
3133 ----
3134 // Insert phi function to $Sink. ----
3135 BuildMI(*Sink, Sink->begin(), DL, TII->get(Mips::PHI), 0
3136 MI.getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
3137 .addReg(RD1) 0
3138 .addMBB(FBB) 0
3139 .addReg(RD2) 0
3140 .addMBB(TBB); 0
3141 ----
3142 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now. 0
3143 return Sink; 0
3144 } 0
3145 ----
3146 // Emit the COPY_FW pseudo instruction. ----
3147 // ----
3148 // copy_fw_pseudo $fd, $ws, n ----
3149 // => ----
3150 // copy_u_w $rt, $ws, $n ----
3151 // mtc1 $rt, $fd ----
3152 // ----
3153 // When n is zero, the equivalent operation can be performed with (potentially) ----
3154 // zero instructions due to register overlaps. This optimization is never valid ----
3155 // for lane 1 because it would require FR=0 mode which isn't supported by MSA. ----
3156 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3157 MipsSETargetLowering::emitCOPY_FW(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3158 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
3159 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3160 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3161 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3162 Register Fd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3163 Register Ws = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3164 unsigned Lane = MI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
3165 ----
3166 if (Lane == 0) { 0
3167 unsigned Wt = Ws; 0
3168 if (!Subtarget.useOddSPReg()) { 0
3169 // We must copy to an even-numbered MSA register so that the ----
3170 // single-precision sub-register is also guaranteed to be even-numbered. ----
3171 Wt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WEvensRegClass); 0
3172 ----
3173 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), Wt).addReg(Ws); 0
3174 } ----
3175 ----
3176 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), Fd).addReg(Wt, 0, Mips::sub_lo); 0
3177 } else { ----
3178 Register Wt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister( 0
3179 Subtarget.useOddSPReg() ? &Mips::MSA128WRegClass 0
3180 : &Mips::MSA128WEvensRegClass); ----
3181 ----
3182 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SPLATI_W), Wt).addReg(Ws).addImm(Lane); 0
3183 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), Fd).addReg(Wt, 0, Mips::sub_lo); 0
3184 } ----
3185 ----
3186 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now. 0
3187 return BB; 0
3188 } 0
3189 ----
3190 // Emit the COPY_FD pseudo instruction. ----
3191 // ----
3192 // copy_fd_pseudo $fd, $ws, n ----
3193 // => ----
3194 // splati.d $wt, $ws, $n ----
3195 // copy $fd, $wt:sub_64 ----
3196 // ----
3197 // When n is zero, the equivalent operation can be performed with (potentially) ----
3198 // zero instructions due to register overlaps. This optimization is always ----
3199 // valid because FR=1 mode which is the only supported mode in MSA. ----
3200 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3201 MipsSETargetLowering::emitCOPY_FD(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3202 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
3203 assert(Subtarget.isFP64bit()); 0
3204 ----
3205 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3206 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3207 Register Fd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3208 Register Ws = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3209 unsigned Lane = MI.getOperand(2).getImm() * 2; 0
3210 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3211 ----
3212 if (Lane == 0) 0
3213 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), Fd).addReg(Ws, 0, Mips::sub_64); 0
3214 else { ----
3215 Register Wt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128DRegClass); 0
3216 ----
3217 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SPLATI_D), Wt).addReg(Ws).addImm(1); 0
3218 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), Fd).addReg(Wt, 0, Mips::sub_64); 0
3219 } ----
3220 ----
3221 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now. 0
3222 return BB; 0
3223 } 0
3224 ----
3225 // Emit the INSERT_FW pseudo instruction. ----
3226 // ----
3227 // insert_fw_pseudo $wd, $wd_in, $n, $fs ----
3228 // => ----
3229 // subreg_to_reg $wt:sub_lo, $fs ----
3230 // insve_w $wd[$n], $wd_in, $wt[0] ----
3231 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3232 MipsSETargetLowering::emitINSERT_FW(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3233 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
3234 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3235 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3236 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3237 Register Wd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3238 Register Wd_in = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3239 unsigned Lane = MI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
3240 Register Fs = MI.getOperand(3).getReg(); 0
3241 Register Wt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister( 0
3242 Subtarget.useOddSPReg() ? &Mips::MSA128WRegClass 0
3243 : &Mips::MSA128WEvensRegClass); ----
3244 ----
3245 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SUBREG_TO_REG), Wt) 0
3246 .addImm(0) 0
3247 .addReg(Fs) 0
3248 .addImm(Mips::sub_lo); 0
3249 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::INSVE_W), Wd) 0
3250 .addReg(Wd_in) 0
3251 .addImm(Lane) 0
3252 .addReg(Wt) 0
3253 .addImm(0); 0
3254 ----
3255 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now. 0
3256 return BB; 0
3257 } 0

3259 // Emit the INSERT_FD pseudo instruction. ----
3260 // ----
3261 // insert_fd_pseudo $wd, $fs, n ----
3262 // => ----

3264 // insve_d $wd[$n], $wd_in, $wt[0] ----
3265 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3266 MipsSETargetLowering::emitINSERT_FD(MachineInstr &MI, 0

3269 ----

3278 ----
3279 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SUBREG_TO_REG), Wt) 0
3280 .addImm(0) 0
