3292 ----
3293 // Emit the INSERT_([BHWD]|F[WD])_VIDX pseudo instruction. ----
3294 // ----
3295 // For integer: ----
3296 // (INSERT_([BHWD]|F[WD])_PSEUDO $wd, $wd_in, $n, $rs) ----
3297 // => ----
3298 // (SLL $lanetmp1, $lane, ----
3299 // (SLD_B $wdtmp1, $wd_in, $wd_in, $lanetmp1) ----
3300 // (INSERT_[BHWD], $wdtmp2, $wdtmp1, 0, $rs) ----
3301 // (NEG $lanetmp2, $lanetmp1) ----
3302 // (SLD_B $wd, $wdtmp2, $wdtmp2, $lanetmp2) ----
3303 // ----
3304 // For floating point: ----
3305 // (INSERT_([BHWD]|F[WD])_PSEUDO $wd, $wd_in, $n, $fs) ----
3306 // => ----
3307 // (SUBREG_TO_REG $wt, $fs, ) ----
3308 // (SLL $lanetmp1, $lane, ----
3309 // (SLD_B $wdtmp1, $wd_in, $wd_in, $lanetmp1) ----
3310 // (INSVE_[WD], $wdtmp2, 0, $wdtmp1, 0) ----
3311 // (NEG $lanetmp2, $lanetmp1) ----
3312 // (SLD_B $wd, $wdtmp2, $wdtmp2, $lanetmp2) ----
3313 MachineBasicBlock *MipsSETargetLowering::emitINSERT_DF_VIDX( 0
3314 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB, unsigned EltSizeInBytes, ----
3315 bool IsFP) const { ----
3316 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3317 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3318 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3319 Register Wd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3320 Register SrcVecReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3321 Register LaneReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
3322 Register SrcValReg = MI.getOperand(3).getReg(); 0
3323 ----
3324 const TargetRegisterClass *VecRC = nullptr; 0
3325 // FIXME: This should be true for N32 too. ----
3326 const TargetRegisterClass *GPRRC = ----
3327 Subtarget.isABI_N64() ? &Mips::GPR64RegClass : &Mips::GPR32RegClass; 0
3328 unsigned SubRegIdx = Subtarget.isABI_N64() ? Mips::sub_32 : 0; 0
3329 unsigned ShiftOp = Subtarget.isABI_N64() ? Mips::DSLL : Mips::SLL; 0
3330 unsigned EltLog2Size; ----
3331 unsigned InsertOp = 0; 0
3332 unsigned InsveOp = 0; 0
3333 switch (EltSizeInBytes) { 0
3334 default: 0
3335 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected size"); 0
3336 case 1: 0
3337 EltLog2Size = 0; 0
3338 InsertOp = Mips::INSERT_B; 0
3339 InsveOp = Mips::INSVE_B; 0
3340 VecRC = &Mips::MSA128BRegClass; 0
3341 break; 0
3342 case 2: 0
3343 EltLog2Size = 1; 0
3344 InsertOp = Mips::INSERT_H; 0
3345 InsveOp = Mips::INSVE_H; 0
3346 VecRC = &Mips::MSA128HRegClass; 0
3347 break; 0
3348 case 4: 0
3349 EltLog2Size = 2; 0
3350 InsertOp = Mips::INSERT_W; 0
3351 InsveOp = Mips::INSVE_W; 0
3352 VecRC = &Mips::MSA128WRegClass; 0
3353 break; 0
3354 case 8: 0
3355 EltLog2Size = 3; 0
3356 InsertOp = Mips::INSERT_D; 0
3357 InsveOp = Mips::INSVE_D; 0
3358 VecRC = &Mips::MSA128DRegClass; 0
3359 break; 0
3360 } ----
3361 ----
3362 if (IsFP) { 0
3363 Register Wt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(VecRC); 0
3364 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SUBREG_TO_REG), Wt) 0
3365 .addImm(0) 0
3366 .addReg(SrcValReg) 0
3367 .addImm(EltSizeInBytes == 8 ? Mips::sub_64 : Mips::sub_lo); 0
3368 SrcValReg = Wt; 0
3369 } ----
3370 ----
3371 // Convert the lane index into a byte index ----
3372 if (EltSizeInBytes != 1) { 0
3373 Register LaneTmp1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(GPRRC); 0
3374 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(ShiftOp), LaneTmp1) 0
3375 .addReg(LaneReg) 0
3376 .addImm(EltLog2Size); 0
3377 LaneReg = LaneTmp1; 0
3378 } ----
3379 ----
3380 // Rotate bytes around so that the desired lane is element zero ----
3381 Register WdTmp1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(VecRC); 0
3382 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLD_B), WdTmp1) 0
3383 .addReg(SrcVecReg) 0
3384 .addReg(SrcVecReg) 0
3385 .addReg(LaneReg, 0, SubRegIdx); 0
3386 ----
3387 Register WdTmp2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(VecRC); 0
3388 if (IsFP) { 0
3389 // Use insve.df to insert to element zero ----
3390 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(InsveOp), WdTmp2) 0
3391 .addReg(WdTmp1) 0
3392 .addImm(0) 0
3393 .addReg(SrcValReg) 0
3394 .addImm(0); 0
3395 } else { ----
3396 // Use insert.df to insert to element zero ----
3397 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(InsertOp), WdTmp2) 0
3398 .addReg(WdTmp1) 0
3399 .addReg(SrcValReg) 0
3400 .addImm(0); 0
3401 } ----
3402 ----
3403 // Rotate elements the rest of the way for a full rotation. ----
3404 // sld.df inteprets $rt modulo the number of columns so we only need to negate ----
3405 // the lane index to do this. ----
3406 Register LaneTmp2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(GPRRC); 0
3407 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Subtarget.isABI_N64() ? Mips::DSUB : Mips::SUB), 0
3408 LaneTmp2) ----
3409 .addReg(Subtarget.isABI_N64() ? Mips::ZERO_64 : Mips::ZERO) 0
3410 .addReg(LaneReg); 0
3411 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLD_B), Wd) 0
3412 .addReg(WdTmp2) 0
3413 .addReg(WdTmp2) 0
3414 .addReg(LaneTmp2, 0, SubRegIdx); 0
3415 ----
3416 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now. 0
3417 return BB; 0
3418 } 0
3419 ----
3420 // Emit the FILL_FW pseudo instruction. ----
3421 // ----
3422 // fill_fw_pseudo $wd, $fs ----
3423 // => ----
3424 // implicit_def $wt1 ----
3425 // insert_subreg $wt2:subreg_lo, $wt1, $fs ----
3426 // splati.w $wd, $wt2[0] ----
3427 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3428 MipsSETargetLowering::emitFILL_FW(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3429 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
3430 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3431 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3432 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3433 Register Wd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3434 Register Fs = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3435 Register Wt1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister( 0
3436 Subtarget.useOddSPReg() ? &Mips::MSA128WRegClass 0
3437 : &Mips::MSA128WEvensRegClass); ----
3438 Register Wt2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister( 0
3439 Subtarget.useOddSPReg() ? &Mips::MSA128WRegClass 0
3440 : &Mips::MSA128WEvensRegClass); ----
3441 ----
3442 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::IMPLICIT_DEF), Wt1); 0
3443 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::INSERT_SUBREG), Wt2) 0
3444 .addReg(Wt1) 0
3445 .addReg(Fs) 0
3446 .addImm(Mips::sub_lo); 0
3447 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SPLATI_W), Wd).addReg(Wt2).addImm(0); 0
3448 ----
3449 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now. 0
3450 return BB; 0
3451 } 0
3452 ----
3453 // Emit the FILL_FD pseudo instruction. ----
3454 // ----
3455 // fill_fd_pseudo $wd, $fs ----
3456 // => ----
3457 // implicit_def $wt1 ----
3458 // insert_subreg $wt2:subreg_64, $wt1, $fs ----
3459 // splati.d $wd, $wt2[0] ----
3460 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3461 MipsSETargetLowering::emitFILL_FD(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3462 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
3463 assert(Subtarget.isFP64bit()); 0
3464 ----
3465 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3466 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3467 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3468 Register Wd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3469 Register Fs = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3470 Register Wt1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128DRegClass); 0
3471 Register Wt2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128DRegClass); 0
3472 ----
3473 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::IMPLICIT_DEF), Wt1); 0
3474 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::INSERT_SUBREG), Wt2) 0
3475 .addReg(Wt1) 0
3476 .addReg(Fs) 0
3477 .addImm(Mips::sub_64); 0
3478 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SPLATI_D), Wd).addReg(Wt2).addImm(0); 0
3479 ----
3480 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now. 0
3481 return BB; 0
3482 } 0
3483 ----
3484 // Emit the ST_F16_PSEDUO instruction to store a f16 value from an MSA ----
3485 // register. ----
3486 // ----
3487 // STF16 MSA128F16:$wd, mem_simm10:$addr ----
3488 // => ----
3489 // copy_u.h $rtemp,$wd[0] ----
3490 // sh $rtemp, $addr ----
3491 // ----
3492 // Safety: We can't use st.h & co as they would over write the memory after ----
3493 // the destination. It would require half floats be allocated 16 bytes(!) of ----
3494 // space. ----
3495 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3496 MipsSETargetLowering::emitST_F16_PSEUDO(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3497 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
3498 ----
3499 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3500 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3501 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3502 Register Ws = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3503 Register Rt = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3504 const MachineMemOperand &MMO = **MI.memoperands_begin(); 0
3505 unsigned Imm = MMO.getOffset(); 0
3506 ----
3507 // Caution: A load via the GOT can expand to a GPR32 operand, a load via ----
3508 // spill and reload can expand as a GPR64 operand. Examine the ----
3509 // operand in detail and default to ABI. ----
3510 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = ----
3511 MI.getOperand(1).isReg() ? RegInfo.getRegClass(MI.getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
3512 : (Subtarget.isABI_O32() ? &Mips::GPR32RegClass 0
3513 : &Mips::GPR64RegClass); 0
3514 const bool UsingMips32 = RC == &Mips::GPR32RegClass; 0
3515 Register Rs = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
3516 ----
3517 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY_U_H), Rs).addReg(Ws).addImm(0); 0
3518 if(!UsingMips32) { 0
3519 Register Tmp = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR64RegClass); 0
3520 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SUBREG_TO_REG), Tmp) 0
3521 .addImm(0) 0
3522 .addReg(Rs) 0
3523 .addImm(Mips::sub_32); 0
3524 Rs = Tmp; 0
3525 } ----
3526 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(UsingMips32 ? Mips::SH : Mips::SH64)) 0
3527 .addReg(Rs) 0
3528 .addReg(Rt) 0
3529 .addImm(Imm) 0
3530 .addMemOperand(BB->getParent()->getMachineMemOperand( 0
3531 &MMO, MMO.getOffset(), MMO.getSize())); ----
3532 ----
3533 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
3534 return BB; 0
3535 } 0
3536 ----
3537 // Emit the LD_F16_PSEDUO instruction to load a f16 value into an MSA register. ----
3538 // ----
3539 // LD_F16 MSA128F16:$wd, mem_simm10:$addr ----
3540 // => ----
3541 // lh $rtemp, $addr ----
3542 // fill.h $wd, $rtemp ----
3543 // ----
3544 // Safety: We can't use ld.h & co as they over-read from the source. ----
3545 // Additionally, if the address is not modulo 16, 2 cases can occur: ----
3546 // a) Segmentation fault as the load instruction reads from a memory page ----
3547 // memory it's not supposed to. ----
3548 // b) The load crosses an implementation specific boundary, requiring OS ----
3549 // intervention. ----
3550 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3551 MipsSETargetLowering::emitLD_F16_PSEUDO(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3552 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
3553 ----
3554 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3555 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3556 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3557 Register Wd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3558 ----
3559 // Caution: A load via the GOT can expand to a GPR32 operand, a load via ----
3560 // spill and reload can expand as a GPR64 operand. Examine the ----
3561 // operand in detail and default to ABI. ----
3562 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = ----
3563 MI.getOperand(1).isReg() ? RegInfo.getRegClass(MI.getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
3564 : (Subtarget.isABI_O32() ? &Mips::GPR32RegClass 0
3565 : &Mips::GPR64RegClass); 0
3566 ----
3567 const bool UsingMips32 = RC == &Mips::GPR32RegClass; 0
3568 Register Rt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
3569 ----
3570 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
3571 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(UsingMips32 ? Mips::LH : Mips::LH64), Rt); 0
3572 for (const MachineOperand &MO : llvm::drop_begin(MI.operands())) 0
3573 MIB.add(MO); 0
3574 ----
3575 if(!UsingMips32) { 0
3576 Register Tmp = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
3577 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), Tmp).addReg(Rt, 0, Mips::sub_32); 0
3578 Rt = Tmp; 0
3579 } ----
3580 ----
3581 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FILL_H), Wd).addReg(Rt); 0
3582 ----
3583 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
3584 return BB; 0
3585 } 0
3586 ----
3587 // Emit the FPROUND_PSEUDO instruction. ----
3588 // ----
3589 // Round an FGR64Opnd, FGR32Opnd to an f16. ----
3590 // ----
3591 // Safety: Cycle the operand through the GPRs so the result always ends up ----
3592 // the correct MSA register. ----
3593 // ----
3594 // FIXME: This copying is strictly unnecessary. If we could tie FGR32Opnd:$Fs ----
3595 // / FGR64Opnd:$Fs and MSA128F16:$Wd to the same physical register ----
3596 // (which they can be, as the MSA registers are defined to alias the ----
3597 // FPU's 64 bit and 32 bit registers) the result can be accessed using ----
3598 // the correct register class. That requires operands be tie-able across ----
3599 // register classes which have a sub/super register class relationship. ----
3600 // ----
3601 // For FPG32Opnd: ----
3602 // ----
3603 // FPROUND MSA128F16:$wd, FGR32Opnd:$fs ----
3604 // => ----
3605 // mfc1 $rtemp, $fs ----
3606 // fill.w $rtemp, $wtemp ----
3607 // fexdo.w $wd, $wtemp, $wtemp ----
3608 // ----
3609 // For FPG64Opnd on mips32r2+: ----
3610 // ----
3611 // FPROUND MSA128F16:$wd, FGR64Opnd:$fs ----
3612 // => ----
3613 // mfc1 $rtemp, $fs ----
3614 // fill.w $rtemp, $wtemp ----
3615 // mfhc1 $rtemp2, $fs ----
3616 // insert.w $wtemp[1], $rtemp2 ----
3617 // insert.w $wtemp[3], $rtemp2 ----
3618 // fexdo.w $wtemp2, $wtemp, $wtemp ----
3619 // fexdo.h $wd, $temp2, $temp2 ----
3620 // ----
3621 // For FGR64Opnd on mips64r2+: ----
3622 // ----
3623 // FPROUND MSA128F16:$wd, FGR64Opnd:$fs ----
3624 // => ----
3625 // dmfc1 $rtemp, $fs ----
3626 // fill.d $rtemp, $wtemp ----
3627 // fexdo.w $wtemp2, $wtemp, $wtemp ----
3628 // fexdo.h $wd, $wtemp2, $wtemp2 ----
3629 // ----
3630 // Safety note: As $wtemp is UNDEF, we may provoke a spurious exception if the ----
3631 // undef bits are "just right" and the exception enable bits are ----
3632 // set. By using fill.w to replicate $fs into all elements over ----
3633 // insert.w for one element, we avoid that potiential case. If ----
3634 // fexdo.[hw] causes an exception in, the exception is valid and it ----
3635 // occurs for all elements. ----
3636 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3637 MipsSETargetLowering::emitFPROUND_PSEUDO(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3638 MachineBasicBlock *BB, ----
3639 bool IsFGR64) const { ----
3640 ----
3641 // Strictly speaking, we need MIPS32R5 to support MSA. We'll be generous ----
3642 // here. It's technically doable to support MIPS32 here, but the ISA forbids ----
3643 // it. ----
3644 assert(Subtarget.hasMSA() && Subtarget.hasMips32r2()); 0
3645 ----
3646 bool IsFGR64onMips64 = Subtarget.hasMips64() && IsFGR64; 0
3647 bool IsFGR64onMips32 = !Subtarget.hasMips64() && IsFGR64; 0
3648 ----
3649 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3650 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3651 Register Wd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3652 Register Fs = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3653 ----
3654 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3655 Register Wtemp = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass); 0
3656 const TargetRegisterClass *GPRRC = 0
3657 IsFGR64onMips64 ? &Mips::GPR64RegClass : &Mips::GPR32RegClass; 0
3658 unsigned MFC1Opc = IsFGR64onMips64 0
3659 ? Mips::DMFC1 0
3660 : (IsFGR64onMips32 ? Mips::MFC1_D64 : Mips::MFC1); ----
3661 unsigned FILLOpc = IsFGR64onMips64 ? Mips::FILL_D : Mips::FILL_W; 0
3662 ----
3663 // Perform the register class copy as mentioned above. ----
3664 Register Rtemp = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(GPRRC); 0
3665 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(MFC1Opc), Rtemp).addReg(Fs); 0
3666 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(FILLOpc), Wtemp).addReg(Rtemp); 0
3667 unsigned WPHI = Wtemp; 0
3668 ----
3669 if (IsFGR64onMips32) { 0
3670 Register Rtemp2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(GPRRC); 0
3671 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::MFHC1_D64), Rtemp2).addReg(Fs); 0
3672 Register Wtemp2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass); 0
3673 Register Wtemp3 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass); 0
3674 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::INSERT_W), Wtemp2) 0
3675 .addReg(Wtemp) 0
3676 .addReg(Rtemp2) 0
3677 .addImm(1); 0
3678 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::INSERT_W), Wtemp3) 0
3679 .addReg(Wtemp2) 0
3680 .addReg(Rtemp2) 0
3681 .addImm(3); 0
3682 WPHI = Wtemp3; 0
3683 } ----
3684 ----
3685 if (IsFGR64) { 0
3686 Register Wtemp2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass); 0
3687 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FEXDO_W), Wtemp2) 0
3688 .addReg(WPHI) 0
3689 .addReg(WPHI); 0
3690 WPHI = Wtemp2; 0
3691 } ----
3692 ----
3693 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FEXDO_H), Wd).addReg(WPHI).addReg(WPHI); 0
3694 ----
3695 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
3696 return BB; 0
3697 } 0
3698 ----
3699 // Emit the FPEXTEND_PSEUDO instruction. ----
3700 // ----
3701 // Expand an f16 to either a FGR32Opnd or FGR64Opnd. ----
3702 // ----
3703 // Safety: Cycle the result through the GPRs so the result always ends up ----
3704 // the correct floating point register. ----
3705 // ----
3706 // FIXME: This copying is strictly unnecessary. If we could tie FGR32Opnd:$Fd ----
3707 // / FGR64Opnd:$Fd and MSA128F16:$Ws to the same physical register ----
3708 // (which they can be, as the MSA registers are defined to alias the ----
3709 // FPU's 64 bit and 32 bit registers) the result can be accessed using ----
3710 // the correct register class. That requires operands be tie-able across ----
3711 // register classes which have a sub/super register class relationship. I ----
3712 // haven't checked. ----
3713 // ----
3714 // For FGR32Opnd: ----
3715 // ----
3716 // FPEXTEND FGR32Opnd:$fd, MSA128F16:$ws ----
3717 // => ----
3718 // fexupr.w $wtemp, $ws ----
3719 // copy_s.w $rtemp, $ws[0] ----
3720 // mtc1 $rtemp, $fd ----
3721 // ----
3722 // For FGR64Opnd on Mips64: ----
3723 // ----
3724 // FPEXTEND FGR64Opnd:$fd, MSA128F16:$ws ----
3725 // => ----
3726 // fexupr.w $wtemp, $ws ----
3727 // fexupr.d $wtemp2, $wtemp ----
3728 // copy_s.d $rtemp, $wtemp2s[0] ----
3729 // dmtc1 $rtemp, $fd ----
3730 // ----
3731 // For FGR64Opnd on Mips32: ----
3732 // ----
3733 // FPEXTEND FGR64Opnd:$fd, MSA128F16:$ws ----
3734 // => ----
3735 // fexupr.w $wtemp, $ws ----
3736 // fexupr.d $wtemp2, $wtemp ----
3737 // copy_s.w $rtemp, $wtemp2[0] ----
3738 // mtc1 $rtemp, $ftemp ----
3739 // copy_s.w $rtemp2, $wtemp2[1] ----
3740 // $fd = mthc1 $rtemp2, $ftemp ----
3741 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3742 MipsSETargetLowering::emitFPEXTEND_PSEUDO(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3743 MachineBasicBlock *BB, ----
3744 bool IsFGR64) const { ----
3745 ----
3746 // Strictly speaking, we need MIPS32R5 to support MSA. We'll be generous ----
3747 // here. It's technically doable to support MIPS32 here, but the ISA forbids ----
3748 // it. ----
3749 assert(Subtarget.hasMSA() && Subtarget.hasMips32r2()); 0
3750 ----
3751 bool IsFGR64onMips64 = Subtarget.hasMips64() && IsFGR64; 0
3752 bool IsFGR64onMips32 = !Subtarget.hasMips64() && IsFGR64; 0
3753 ----
3754 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3755 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3756 Register Fd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3757 Register Ws = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3758 ----
3759 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3760 const TargetRegisterClass *GPRRC = 0
3761 IsFGR64onMips64 ? &Mips::GPR64RegClass : &Mips::GPR32RegClass; 0
3762 unsigned MTC1Opc = IsFGR64onMips64 0
3763 ? Mips::DMTC1 0
3764 : (IsFGR64onMips32 ? Mips::MTC1_D64 : Mips::MTC1); ----
3765 Register COPYOpc = IsFGR64onMips64 ? Mips::COPY_S_D : Mips::COPY_S_W; 0
3766 ----
3767 Register Wtemp = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass); 0
3768 Register WPHI = Wtemp; 0
3769 ----
3770 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FEXUPR_W), Wtemp).addReg(Ws); 0
3771 if (IsFGR64) { 0
3772 WPHI = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128DRegClass); 0
3773 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FEXUPR_D), WPHI).addReg(Wtemp); 0
3774 } ----
3775 ----
3776 // Perform the safety regclass copy mentioned above. ----
3777 Register Rtemp = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(GPRRC); 0
3778 Register FPRPHI = IsFGR64onMips32 ----
3779 ? RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::FGR64RegClass) 0
3780 : Fd; 0
3781 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(COPYOpc), Rtemp).addReg(WPHI).addImm(0); 0
3782 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(MTC1Opc), FPRPHI).addReg(Rtemp); 0
3783 ----
3784 if (IsFGR64onMips32) { 0
3785 Register Rtemp2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(GPRRC); 0
3786 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY_S_W), Rtemp2) 0
3787 .addReg(WPHI) 0
3788 .addImm(1); 0
3789 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::MTHC1_D64), Fd) 0
3790 .addReg(FPRPHI) 0
3791 .addReg(Rtemp2); 0
3792 } ----
3793 ----
3794 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
3795 return BB; 0
3796 } 0
3797 ----
3798 // Emit the FEXP2_W_1 pseudo instructions. ----
3799 // ----
3800 // fexp2_w_1_pseudo $wd, $wt ----
3801 // => ----
3802 // ldi.w $ws, 1 ----
3803 // fexp2.w $wd, $ws, $wt ----
3804 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3805 MipsSETargetLowering::emitFEXP2_W_1(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3806 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
3807 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3808 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3809 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &Mips::MSA128WRegClass; 0
3810 Register Ws1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
3811 Register Ws2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
3812 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3813 ----
3814 // Splat 1.0 into a vector ----
3815 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::LDI_W), Ws1).addImm(1); 0
3816 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FFINT_U_W), Ws2).addReg(Ws1); 0
3817 ----
3818 // Emit 1.0 * fexp2(Wt) ----
3819 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FEXP2_W), MI.getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
3820 .addReg(Ws2) 0
3821 .addReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
3822 ----
3823 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now. 0
3824 return BB; 0
3825 } 0
3826 ----
3827 // Emit the FEXP2_D_1 pseudo instructions. ----
3828 // ----
3829 // fexp2_d_1_pseudo $wd, $wt ----
3830 // => ----
3831 // ldi.d $ws, 1 ----
3832 // fexp2.d $wd, $ws, $wt ----
3833 MachineBasicBlock * ----
3834 MipsSETargetLowering::emitFEXP2_D_1(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3835 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
3836 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
3837 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
3838 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &Mips::MSA128DRegClass; 0
3839 Register Ws1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
3840 Register Ws2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
3841 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
3842 ----
3843 // Splat 1.0 into a vector ----
3844 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::LDI_D), Ws1).addImm(1); 0
3845 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FFINT_U_D), Ws2).addReg(Ws1); 0
3846 ----
3847 // Emit 1.0 * fexp2(Wt) ----
3848 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FEXP2_D), MI.getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
3849 .addReg(Ws2) 0
3850 .addReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
3851 ----
3852 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now. 0
3853 return BB; 0
3854 } 0
